1
00:00:57,960 --> 00:01:00,660
GORDON:
1 knew Harvey Dent.

2
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,089
1 was his friend.

3
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:10,560
And it will be a very long time before
someone inspires us the way he did.

4
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:15,190
I believed in Harvey Dent.

5
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:36,070
Dr. Pavel, I'm CIA.

6
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,430
DRIVER:
He wasn't alone.

7
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:41,130
-Uh, you don't get to bring friends.
-They are not my friends.

8
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:43,440
DRIVER:
Don't worry, no charge for them.

9
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:47,040
CIA OP: And why would I want them?
DRIVER: They were trying to grab your prize.

10
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:49,050
They work for the mercenary.

11
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,020
The masked man.

12
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,840
-Bane?
-Aye.

13
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,520
Get them onboard. I'll call it in.

14
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,960
CIA OP: The flight plan I just filed
with the agency...

15
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:10,950
.. lists me, my men, Dr. Pavel here...

16
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,460
..but only one of you!

17
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:20,170
First one to talk gets to stay on my aircraft!

18
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:30,450
Who paid you to grab Dr. Pavel?

19
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,440
[GUNSHOT]

20
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:37,440
He didn't fly so good!

21
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:39,560
Who wants to try next?

22
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:42,090
Tell me about Bane!

23
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,700
Why does he wear the mask?

24
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,560
A lot of loyalty for a hired gun!

25
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,090
MAN: Well, perhaps he's wondering
why someone would shoot a man...

26
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:55,310
..before throwing him out of a plane.

27
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,920
At least you can talk.

28
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,220
Who are you?

29
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,590
MAN:
It doesn't matter who we are.

30
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,140
What matters is our plan.

31
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:16,359
No one cared who I was
till l put on the mask.

32
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,960
If I pull that off, will you die?

33
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:22,180
BANE:
It would be extremely painful.

34
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,590
You're a big guy.

35
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:24,890
BANE:
For you.

36
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,690
Was getting caught part of your plan?

37
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,400
BANE:
Of course.

38
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:40,269
Dr. Pavel refused our offer in favor of yours.

39
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:43,790
-We had to find out what he told you--
-Nothing. I said nothing.

40
00:03:57,040 --> 00:04:00,019
Well, congratulations,
you got yourself caught!

41
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:03,480
-Sir?
-What's the next step of your master plan?

42
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,160
BANE:
Crashing this plane...

43
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,739
..With no survivors.

44
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,550
[GUNFIRE]

45
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,190
PILOT:
Mayday, Mayday!

46
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,490
[YELLS]

47
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,890
[GRUNTING]

48
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:23,350
Aah! What you doing to me? Let me out!

49
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,719
No!

50
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,880
No, no, no! No!

51
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,390
[PAVEL YELLING]

52
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,640
BANE: No! They expect one of us
in the wreckage, brother.

53
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,270
Have we started the fire?

54
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,630
BANE:
Yes, the fire rises.

55
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,110
[PAVEL YELLING]

56
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:02,620
Calm down, doctor.
Now is not the time for fear.

57
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,120
That comes later.

58
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:34,040
MAYOR: Harvey Dent Day
may not be our oldest public holiday...

59
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:37,200
..but we're here tonight
because it's one of the most important.

60
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:41,200
Harvey Dent's uncompromising stand
against organized crime...

61
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:45,320
..had made Gotham a safer place than it was
at the time of his death, eight years ago.

62
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,630
This city has seen a historic turnaround.

63
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:51,020
No city is without crime...

64
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,940
..but this city is without
organized crime because the Dent Act...

65
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:57,140
..gave law enforcement teeth
in its fight against the mob.

66
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,770
Now people are talking about
repealing the Dent Act...

67
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,890
..and to them I say, "Not on my watch."

68
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,380
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDS]

69
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:08,000
I want to thank the Wayne Foundation
for hosting this event.

70
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:11,960
I'm told Mr. Wayne couldn't be here tonight.
I'm sure he's with us in spirit.

71
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,920
And now I'm gonna give way
to an important voice....

72
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:17,469
CONGRESSMAN: You ever lay eyes
on Wayne at one of these things?

73
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,360
No one has. Not in years.

74
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:22,980
MAYOR: --people put their faith
in a murderous thug in a mask and a cape.

75
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,580
Athug who showed his true nature...

76
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,230
..when he betrayed the trust
of this great man...

77
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,890
..and murdered him in cold blood.

78
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,760
Sweetheart, not so fast with the chow.

79
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,880
-Shrimp balls?
-Thank you.

80
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:40,190
Jim Gordon can tell you the truth about
Harvey Dent. I'll let him tell you himself.

81
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:41,990
Commissioner Gordon.

82
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,350
GORDON:
The truth?

83
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,320
I have...

84
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,090
.. written a speech...

85
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,790
..telling the truth about Harvey Dent.

86
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,700
Maybe the time isn't right.

87
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,770
Maybe right now...

88
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,450
.all you need to know
is that there are...

89
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:25,020
...1000 inmates in Blackgate Prison
as a direct result of the Dent Act.

90
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:29,820
These are violent criminals, essential cogs
in the organized-crime machine.

91
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:34,710
Maybe, for now, all I should say
about the death of Harvey Dent is this:

92
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,380
It has not been for nothing.

93
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,429
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDS]

94
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:45,040
MAID 1: You see the owner of the house?
MAID 2: No. f heard...

95
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:48,010
-..he never leaves the east wing.
-[ heard he had an accident.

96
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:51,680
-That he's disfigured. He has to wear a--
ALFRED: Mr. Till?

97
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:55,420
Why are your people
using the main staircase?

98
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,010
And where's Mrs. Bolton?

99
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,760
SELINA:
Uh, she's at the bar, sir. Can I help?

100
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,170
The east drawing room.

101
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:06,690
Unlock the door, put the tray on the table,
lock the door again. Nothing more.

102
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:13,160
ALFRED: I'm sorry, Miss Tate.
tried, but he won't see you.

103
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,310
And you mustn't take it personally.

104
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:19,070
Everyone knows that Wayne's holed up
in there with 8-inch nails...

105
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:21,079
..peeing into Mason jars.

106
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,440
It's very good of you
to let me on the grounds.

107
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:38,369
DAGGETT: Why are you wasting your time
trying to talk to a man...

108
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:42,890
..who threw away your investment
on some save-the-world vanity project?

109
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,490
He can't get your money back. I can.

110
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:50,210
I could try explaining that
a save-the-world project, vain or not...

111
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:52,910
..is worth investing in, Mr. Daggett.

112
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:56,030
But you understand only money
and the power you think it buys...

113
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:59,060
..SO why waste my time indeed?

114
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:01,180
GORDON:
Second shift reports in?

115
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:03,270
You should spend more time
with the mayor.

116
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:05,260
Well, that's your department.

117
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,950
CONGRESSMAN:
Anyone shown him the crime stats?

118
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:11,090
He goes by his gut and it bothers him,
no matter what the numbers.

119
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:14,900
-Must be popular with his wife.
-Not really. She took the kids to Cleveland.

120
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:19,069
He'll have plenty of time for visits.
The mayor's gonna dump him in the spring.

121
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,020
-Really?
-Mm-hm.

122
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,620
-But he's a hero.
-A war hero. This is peacetime.

123
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:53,550
[SHRIEKS]

124
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:56,840
Oh, sorry, sorry.
I'm so terribly sorry, Mr. Wayne.

125
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,000
It is Mr. Wayne, isn't it?

126
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:08,010
Although you don't have the long nails
or, heh, the facial scars, sir.

127
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,349
Is that what they say about me?

128
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:14,380
It's just that no one ever sees you.

129
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:18,460
That's a beautiful necklace. Reminds me
of one that belonged to my mother.

130
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:21,680
It can't be the same one...

131
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:25,189
..because her pearls are in this safe...

132
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:29,359
..the manufacturer clearly explained...

133
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,840
«is uncrackable.

134
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,560
Oops.

135
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,780
Nobody told me it was uncrackable.

136
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:46,750
I'm afraid I can't let you take those.

137
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:50,590
Look, you wouldn't beat up a woman
any more than I would beat up a cripple.

138
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:55,290
Of course, sometimes
exceptions have to be made.

139
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,510
Good night, Mr. Wayne.

140
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:18,439
Can I have a ride?

141
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,060
You read my mind.

142
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,260
Let's go.

143
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,910
ALFRED:
Miss Tate was asking to see you again.

144
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:26,650
WAYNE:
She's very persistent.

145
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,960
And quite lovely,
in case you were wondering.

146
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,220
-I wasn't.
-What are you doing?

147
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:34,410
Examining print dust.
We've been robbed.

148
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:37,450
And this is your idea
of, uh, sounding the alarm, is it?

149
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,780
She took the pearls,
tracking device and all.

150
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,280
-She?
-One of the maids.

151
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,810
Perhaps you should stop letting them
in this side of the house.

152
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,350
Perhaps you should start learning
to make your own bed.

153
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:50,230
-Why were you dusting for prints?
-I wasn't.

154
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,630
She was.

155
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:58,520
Sir. Congressman Gilly's wife
has been calling in.

156
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:02,300
The congressman never made it home
after the Wayne Foundation event.

157
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,800
That's a job for the police?

158
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:07,550
When you and Dent cleaned the streets,
you cleaned them good.

159
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:11,230
Pretty soon we'll be chasing down, uh,
overdue library books.

160
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,030
[GORDON CHUCKLES]

161
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:16,870
And yet here you are, like we're still at war.

162
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,130
-What's your name, son?
-Blake, sir.

163
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:23,069
You have something you want to ask me?

164
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:28,250
It's about that night. This night,
eight years ago. The night Dent died.

165
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,449
The last confirmed sighting of the Batman.

166
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,470
He murders those people,
takes down two SWAT teams...

167
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:37,120
..breaks Dent's neck
and then just vanishes?

168
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,960
I'm not hearing a question, son.

169
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,050
Don't you want to know who he was?

170
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,150
I know exactly who he was.

171
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:49,030
He was the Batman.

172
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,030
[GORDON SIGHS]

173
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,680
Let's go see about the congressman's wife.

174
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:03,710
ALFRED:
Master Wayne?

175
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,250
Master Wayne?

176
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,080
You haven't been down here in a long time.

177
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:42,500
Trying to find out more about
our jewel thief. I ran her prints.

178
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:44,600
Unless she's lost a lot of weight...

179
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:48,000
..she was wearing
someone else's fingerprints.

180
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,380
She's good.

181
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:52,660
She may be, but we have a trace
on the necklace.

182
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,450
We do. I cross-referenced the address
she went back to...

183
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:58,939
..with police data
on high-end B-and-E's, and, um....

184
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:01,310
Selina Kyle.

185
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:05,750
The databases are full of close-calls,
tips from fences.

186
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:09,850
She's good, but the ground
is shrinking beneath her feet.

187
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,800
We should send the police
before she fences the pearls.

188
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,140
She won't. She likes them too much.

189
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,069
And they weren't what she was after.

190
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:19,190
-What was she after?
-My fingerprints.

191
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:22,130
It was printer toner
mixed with graphite on the safe.

192
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:24,810
It gives a good pull and it's untraceable.

193
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,670
Fascinating. You two should
exchange notes over coffee.

194
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,089
You're trying to set me up
with a jewel thief?

195
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:34,280
I'd set you up with a chimpanzee,
if it brought you back to the world.

196
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,850
There's nothing out there for me.

197
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,620
And that's the problem.

198
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:41,100
You hung up your cape and your cowl
but you didn't move on.

199
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:43,489
You never went to find a life.
To find someone.

200
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,079
Alfred...

201
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,710
.1 did find someone.

202
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,270
I know, and you lost them.

203
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,250
But that's all part of living, sir.

204
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:55,120
But you're not living, you're just waiting,
hoping for things to go bad again.

205
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,030
Remember when you left Gotham?

206
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:59,890
Before all this, before Batman?

207
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,830
You were gone seven years.

208
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:05,980
Seven years I waited,
hoping that you wouldn't come back.

209
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:09,729
Every year, I took a holiday.
I went to Florence.

210
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:12,210
There's this café
on the banks of the Arno.

211
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:15,380
Every fine evening I'd sit there
and order a Fernet Branca.

212
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,420
I had this fantasy...

213
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:22,010
..that I would look across the tables...

214
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:25,870
.and I'd see you there, with a wife.

215
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:27,990
Maybe a couple of kids.

216
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:33,460
You wouldn't say anything to me,
nor me to you.

217
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:38,280
But we'd both know that you'd made it.

218
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,930
That you were happy.

219
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:47,000
I never wanted you to come back to Gotham.

220
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:52,349
l always knew there was nothing here
for you, except pain and tragedy.

221
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:55,459
And I wanted something
more for you than that.

222
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,720
I still do.

223
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:08,350
DWP MAN: They wash up here
a couple of times a month.

224
00:17:08,839 --> 00:17:10,069
More when it gets colder.

225
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,050
Homeless, sheltering in the tunnels.

226
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:17,360
We pulled him from the basin,
but other than that we didn’t touch him.

227
00:17:20,119 --> 00:17:21,489
ROSS: What?
BLAKE: Name's Jimmy.

228
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:23,030
He's from St. Swithin’'s.

229
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:27,099
It's the boys’ home
where I coach some ball.

230
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,680
REILLY:
Jimmy hadn't been around for months.

231
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:34,139
BLAKE: No? Why?
-Blake, you know why.

232
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:37,830
He aged out. We don't have the resources
to keep boys on after 16.

233
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,190
I thought the Wayne Foundation
gave money for that.

234
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,350
Not for the past couple of years.

235
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:45,990
-He has a brother here, doesn't he?
-Mark. I'll tell him.

236
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:49,129
I'd like to, if that's all right.

237
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,310
You know what he was doing
in the tunnels?

238
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:55,950
Lot of guys been going down the tunnels
when they age out.

239
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,350
Say you can live down there.

240
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,540
Say there's work down there.

241
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:04,140
Work?

242
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,850
What kind of work are you
gonna find in the sewers?

243
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:09,530
More than you can find up here, I guess.

244
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,730
BLAKE:
So you know about him?

245
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,090
Of course.

246
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:16,390
Do you think he's coming back?

247
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:19,800
I don't know.

248
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,520
STRYVER:
You brought a date?

249
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:37,580
l like having someone around
to open doors for me.

250
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,590
Right hand. No partials.

251
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:47,750
-Very nice.
-Mm-hm.

252
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:50,560
Not so fast, handsome.

253
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:52,129
You got something for me?

254
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,060
Ah, yes.

255
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,190
[SIGHS]

256
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:07,030
I don't know what you're planning to do
with Mr. Wayne's prints...

257
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:09,909
..but I'm guessing you'll need his thumb.

258
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,750
You don't count so good, huh?

259
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:14,210
I count fine.

260
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:17,430
In fact, I'm counting to 10 right now.

261
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:21,030
Okay.

262
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:27,370
My friend's outside. Just hit "send."

263
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:32,810
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

264
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,080
This place is a little dead.

265
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:43,140
It'll liven up in a minute. Trust me.

266
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:45,980
Is everything okay?

267
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:47,960
Great. Catch you later.

268
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:52,390
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

269
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,800
Hmm.

270
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,560
It would have been a lot easier...

271
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:58,889
..to just give me what we agreed.

272
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:01,320
We can't have loose ends.

273
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:05,000
And even in that dress,
no one's gonna miss you.

274
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:06,860
SELINA:
No.

275
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,780
But my friend over there?

276
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:11,830
Every cop in the city's missing him.

277
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,479
STRYVER:
That's cute.

278
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:16,080
But they're not gonna be looking
in a place like this.

279
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:19,040
I don't know.
You did just use his cell phone.

280
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:23,940
[TIRES SCREECHING NEARBY]

281
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,320
SWAT 1: Go!
SWAT 2: Go!

282
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:47,520
SWAT 3:
Police! Get down now!

283
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:49,590
[SCREAMING]

284
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,820
SELINA:
Help me! Help me!

285
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:53,840
Help me, please! Please help me!

286
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:57,250
[SOBS]

287
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:59,040
[GUNFIRE OUTSIDE]

288
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:06,080
Keep some pressure on that, sweetheart.

289
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:09,780
Call me?

290
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:14,690
BLAKE: You okay, miss?
-He's bleeding. You gotta help him.

291
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:20,950
I got the congressman.

292
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:39,939
[SIRENS WAIL]

293
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:49,919
SWAT 4:
Clear!

294
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:57,370
GORDON: Manhole! Get this up!
Get the DWP down here!

295
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:00,060
You three, down with me.

296
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:03,280
You two, you go down,
cover the next exit!

297
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:20,800
What, they went down there?

298
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,010
[GORDON GRUNTS]

299
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:53,790
-We're gonna go down there, right?
FOLEY: That was a gas explosion, kid.

300
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:57,060
-Wasn't gas. It's a sewer.
-No one goes in till we know what's there.

301
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,139
We know, sir. The police commissioner.

302
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,060
Someone get this hothead out of here?

303
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:03,540
And where's that DWP guy?

304
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,370
BANE:
Why are you here?

305
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:48,030
[GORDON GRUNTS]

306
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:49,620
Answer him.

307
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,010
BANE:
I was asking you.

308
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,899
It's the police commissioner.

309
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:00,790
BANE:
And you brought him down here?

310
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,890
MERCENARY 1: We didn't know what to do.
BANE: You panicked.

311
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:07,210
And your weakness has cost the lives
of three others.

312
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:08,660
No, he's alone.

313
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:11,750
[NECK SNAPS]

314
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:13,820
BANE:
Search him.

315
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,460
Then I will kill you.

316
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,129
[MERCENARIES SHOUTING]

317
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:46,420
-He's dead.
BANE: So show me his body.

318
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:49,800
The water runs to any one of the outflows.
We'd never find him.

319
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,820
BANE: Follow him!
MERCENARY 2: Follow him?

320
00:24:58,240 --> 00:24:59,110
[GUNSHOT]

321
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,710
You okay? You okay?

322
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,689
Hey, hey, you awake?

323
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,379
[GORDON COUGHING]

324
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:20,750
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

325
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,649
I need to see Bruce Wayne.

326
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,070
I'm sorry, Mr. Wayne doesn't take
unscheduled calls.

327
00:25:27,520 --> 00:25:29,030
Even from a police officer.

328
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:32,490
And if I go get a warrant for
the investigation of Harvey Dent's murder?

329
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:34,939
That still count as unscheduled?

330
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:40,920
WAYNE:
What can I do for you, officer?

331
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:43,230
BLAKE:
Commissioner Gordon's been shot.

332
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,440
He chased a gunman
down into the sewers.

333
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:50,649
When I pulled him out, he was babbling
about an underground army.

334
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,740
A masked man called Bane.

335
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:55,720
Shouldn't you be telling
your superior officers?

336
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:58,760
They asked me if he saw
any giant alligators.

337
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:01,000
He needs you.

338
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:03,800
He needs the Batman.

339
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:08,830
-If Commissioner Gordon thinks--
-Oh, he doesn't know or care who you are.

340
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:11,690
But we've met before.

341
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:16,480
It was a long time ago. I was a kid.
Uh, St. Swithin's.

342
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:20,719
It used to be funded by
the Wayne Foundation. It's an orphanage.

343
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:25,560
My mom died when I was small. It was
a car accident, I don't really remember it.

344
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:30,990
But my dad got shot a couple years later
over a gambling debt...

345
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:34,580
..and I remember that one just fine.

346
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:38,700
Not a lot of people know
what it feels like, do they?

347
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,870
To be angry...

348
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,340
..in your bones.

349
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,820
I mean, they understand.

350
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:49,830
Foster parents.

351
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,840
Everybody understands...

352
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:53,620
..for a while.

353
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:57,639
And then they want the angry little kid
to do something he knows he can't do.

354
00:26:58,640 --> 00:26:59,550
Move on.

355
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,890
So after a while,
they stop understanding.

356
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:03,860
They send the angry kid to a boys' home.

357
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:07,630
I figured it out too late.
You gotta learn to hide the anger.

358
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,720
Practice smiling in a mirror.

359
00:27:12,760 --> 00:27:14,020
It's like putting on a mask.

360
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:18,380
So you showed up this one day,
in a cool car.

361
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:20,500
Pretty girl on your arm.

362
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:23,270
We were so excited.

363
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:25,930
Bruce Wayne, billionaire orphan.

364
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:29,840
I mean, we used to make up stories
about you, man. Legends.

365
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:33,630
And, you know, with the other kids,
that's all it was, just stories, but....

366
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:37,530
Right when I saw you,
I knew who you really were.

367
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:41,550
I'd seen that look on your face before.

368
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:44,670
It's the same one I taught myself.

369
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:49,220
I don't know why you took the fall
for Dent's murder...

370
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,120
..but I'm still a believer in the Batman...

371
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:54,560
.even if you're not.

372
00:27:57,360 --> 00:28:01,500
Why did you say that your boys’ home used
to be funded by the Wayne Foundation?

373
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,710
BLAKE:
Because the money stopped.

374
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:07,629
Might be time to get some fresh air.
Start paying attention to the details.

375
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,960
Some of those details
might need your help.

376
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:14,080
WAYNE:
You check that name? Bane?

377
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:16,650
ALFRED: He's a mercenary.
No other known names.

378
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:19,189
Him and his men were behind
a coup in West Africa...

379
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:23,430
..that secured mining operations
for our friend John Daggett.

380
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,990
WAYNE: Now Daggett's brought them here.
-Or so it seems.

381
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:31,110
-I'll keep digging.
-Yeah.

382
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:37,750
Alfred, why did the Wayne Foundation
stop funding boys’ homes in the city?

383
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:42,920
The foundation is funded by
the profits of Wayne Enterprises.

384
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:45,139
There have to be some.

385
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:48,290
-Time to talk to Mr. Fox, I think.
-I'll get him on the phone.

386
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:52,209
No, no, no. Do we still have
any cars around the place?

387
00:28:52,840 --> 00:28:54,419
Yes. One or two.

388
00:28:54,800 --> 00:28:56,480
I need an appointment at the hospital
for my leg.

389
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:59,200
-Which hospital?
-Whichever one Jim Gordon's in.

390
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:06,070
DOCTOR: I have seen worse knees.
WAYNE: That's good.

391
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:08,659
No. That's because there is
no cartilage in your knee.

392
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:11,929
And not much of any use
in your elbows or your shoulders.

393
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:14,480
Between that and the scar tissue
on your kidneys...

394
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:17,170
..the residual concussive damage
to your brain tissue...

395
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:19,890
..and the general scarred-over quality
of your body...

396
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:22,820
-.. can't recommend that you go heli-skiing.
-Right.

397
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,100
We were in this together...

398
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:43,740
..then you were gone.

399
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:45,870
WAYNE:
The Batman wasn't needed anymore.

400
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:48,910
-We won.
-Based on a lie.

401
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:55,770
And now there's evil rising
from where we tried to bury it.

402
00:29:56,680 --> 00:30:00,440
The Batman has to come back.

403
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:03,189
What if he doesn't exist anymore?

404
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:04,720
He must.

405
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:06,720
He must.

406
00:30:20,120 --> 00:30:21,659
YUPPIE:
You took my goddamn wallet, didn't you?

407
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:24,460
-You f-- You took my wallet!
-No, I--

408
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:27,340
-Get out.
YUPPIE: She took my-- Ah!

409
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:29,930
-Now.
YUPPIE: Creep!

410
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:32,860
I don't know what he's so upset about.
There's only 60 bucks in here.

411
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,830
Probably the watch.

412
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:36,770
[CHUCKLES]

413
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,610
[CHATTERING]

414
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:50,550
MAN 1:
Who's that?

415
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:52,629
MAN 2:
A stiff can barely climb out of his sports car.

416
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:54,830
-No, that's Bruce Wayne!
-Mr. Wayne, over here!

417
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:56,430
[ALL SHOUTING]

418
00:30:56,760 --> 00:30:58,650
[BUTTON BEEPS & DEVICES POWER OFF]

419
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:01,920
WAYNE: I'm not sure if my assistant--
-Right through here.

420
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:03,620
Thank you so much.

421
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:05,790
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

422
00:31:08,840 --> 00:31:12,030
MIRANDA:
Bruce Wayne at a charity ball.

423
00:31:13,480 --> 00:31:15,060
Miss Tate, isn't it?

424
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:18,800
Even before you became a recluse,
you never came to these things.

425
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:22,439
The proceeds go to the big fat spread.
It's not about charity.

426
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:26,650
It's about feeding the ego
of whichever society hag laid this on.

427
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:29,670
Actually, this is my party, Mr. Wayne.

428
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,540
Oh.

429
00:31:32,080 --> 00:31:36,399
And the proceeds will go where they should,
because I paid for the big fat spread myself.

430
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:38,560
That's very generous of you.

431
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:42,190
You have to invest if you want to restore
balance to the world.

432
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:44,270
Take our clean-energy project.

433
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:47,210
Sometimes the investment
doesn't pay off.

434
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:51,370
-I'm sorry.
-You have a practiced apathy, Mr. Wayne.

435
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:56,280
But a man who doesn't care about the world
doesn't spend half his fortune to save it.

436
00:31:57,840 --> 00:32:00,370
And isn't so wounded when it fails...

437
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,489
..that he goes into hiding.

438
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,830
Have a good evening, Mr. Wayne.

439
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,360
WAYNE:
Mind if I cut in?

440
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,139
Thank you.

441
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:16,750
[WAYNE CHUCKLES]

442
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,790
-You don't seem happy to see me.
-You were supposed to be a shut-in.

443
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:21,899
I felt like some fresh air.

444
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,670
Why didn't you call the police?

445
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:27,490
I have a powerful friend
who deals with things like this.

446
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:31,580
That's a brazen costume for a cat burglar.

447
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:34,770
Yeah? Who are you pretending to be?

448
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,520
Bruce Wayne, eccentric billionaire.

449
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:40,560
-Who's your date?
SELINA: His wife's in Ibiza.

450
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:44,150
She left her diamonds behind, though.
Worried they might get stolen.

451
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:46,480
It's pronounced "Ibiza."

452
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:50,370
You wouldn't want these folks realizing
you're a crook, not a social climber.

453
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:53,590
You think I care what anyone
in this room thinks of me?

454
00:32:55,560 --> 00:32:57,520
I doubt you care what anyone
in any room thinks of you.

455
00:32:57,960 --> 00:33:01,080
Don't condescend, Mr. Wayne.
You don't know a thing about me.

456
00:33:02,120 --> 00:33:05,669
Well, Selina Kyle, ! know you came here
from your walk-up in Old Town.

457
00:33:06,320 --> 00:33:07,860
A modest place for a master jewel thief.

458
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:11,010
Which means that either
you're saving for retirement...

459
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,750
..or you're in deep with the wrong people.

460
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:18,610
Don't judge me because you were born
in the master bedroom of Wayne Manor.

461
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:22,890
-Actually, l was born in the Regency Room.
-I started out doing what I had to.

462
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:27,360
Once you've done what you had to,
they never let you do what you want to.

463
00:33:27,920 --> 00:33:28,970
Start fresh.

464
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:31,980
Ugh. There's no fresh start in today's world.

465
00:33:32,520 --> 00:33:35,080
Any 12-year-old with a cell phone
could find out what you did.

466
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:38,790
Everything we do is collated
and quantified. Everything sticks.

467
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:41,480
Is that how you justify stealing?

468
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:44,050
I take what I need from those
who have more than enough.

469
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:46,450
I don't stand on the shoulders
of people with less.

470
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:47,750
Robin Hood?

471
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:51,520
I think I'd do more to help someone than
most of the people in this room. Than you.

472
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,670
You think maybe you're assuming
a little too much?

473
00:33:55,080 --> 00:33:58,490
Maybe you're being unrealistic about what's
really in your pants other than your wallet.

474
00:33:59,120 --> 00:33:59,989
Ouch.

475
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:04,879
You think all this can last?
There's a storm coming, Mr. Wayne.

476
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:09,630
You and your friends better batten down
the hatches, because when it hits...

477
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:13,540
«you're all gonna wonder how you
ever thought you could live so large...

478
00:34:14,159 --> 00:34:16,759
and leave so little for the rest of us.

479
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:22,380
You sound like
you're looking forward to it.

480
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:25,370
I'm adaptable.

481
00:34:25,719 --> 00:34:28,459
Those pearls do look better on you
than they did in my safe.

482
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:31,420
But I still can't let you keep them.

483
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:40,860
MAN:
You-- You scared her off!

484
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:45,220
Not likely.

485
00:34:47,440 --> 00:34:48,600
Must have lost my ticket.

486
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:51,240
-Your wife said you were taking a cab home.
-My wife?

487
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:00,470
Just you, sir?

488
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:05,279
Don't worry, Master Wayne.

489
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:08,799
Takes a little time to get back
in the swing of things.

490
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:13,979
Bruce Wayne, as I live and breathe.

491
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:18,080
What brings you out of cryo-sleep,
Mr. Wayne?

492
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:19,990
You haven't lost your sense of humor.

493
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:22,460
Even if you have lost most of my money.

494
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:24,180
Actually, you did that.

495
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,800
If you funnel your entire R and D budget...

496
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:29,740
..into a fusion project
that you then mothball...

497
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:32,200
«your company is unlikely to thrive.

498
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:33,509
What are my options?

499
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,800
Well, if you're unwilling
to turn on the machine...

500
00:35:36,920 --> 00:35:38,460
I can't. I can't, Lucius.

501
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:40,540
Well, then sit tight.

502
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,320
Your majority keeps Daggett at bay...

503
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:46,049
..while we figure out a future for
the energy program with Miranda Tate.

504
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:48,890
She has supported the project
all the way.

505
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:52,270
She's smart. And quite lovely.

506
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:56,160
We all just want what's best for you, Bruce.

507
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:58,709
Show her the machine.

508
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:00,880
I'll think it over.

509
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,319
Anything else?

510
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,529
Nope. Why?

511
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:08,370
These conversations used to end
with an unusual request.

512
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:10,750
I retired.

513
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:14,640
Mm-hm. Well, let me show you
some stuff anyway.

514
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:20,340
Just for old times’ sake.

515
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:26,520
WAYNE: I figured you'd have
shut this place down.

516
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:29,170
FOX:
Oh, it was always shut down, officially.

517
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:30,549
WAYNE:
All this new stuff.

518
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:34,740
FOX: After your father died, we
set up 14 different defense subsidiaries.

519
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:37,690
For years, I've been shuttering
and consolidating...

520
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:40,160
.all the different prototypes
under one roof.

521
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:42,040
-My roof.
-Why?

522
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:44,770
Keep them from falling
into the wrong hands.

523
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:49,830
Oh, now you're just showing off.

524
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:55,140
Defense Department projects
for tight geometry urban pacification.

525
00:36:56,160 --> 00:37:00,020
Rotors are configured to maneuver
between buildings without recirculation.

526
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,260
What's it called?

527
00:37:03,040 --> 00:37:06,590
Oh, it has a long, uninteresting
Wayne Enterprises designation.

528
00:37:07,240 --> 00:37:10,080
I just took to calling it the Bat.

529
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:13,570
And, yes, Mr. Wayne, it does come in black.

530
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:18,089
Works fine, except for the autopilot.

531
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:20,490
Takes a better mind than mine to fix it.

532
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:22,040
Better mind?

533
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:25,270
Well, l was trying to be modest.

534
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,570
Aless busy mind.

535
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:29,279
Yours.

536
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,240
[CRACKING]
[WAYNE GROANING]

537
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:39,589
ALFRED: Is it really painful?
-You're very welcome to try it, Alfred.

538
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:41,600
Happy watching. Thank you, sir.

539
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:45,990
Not bad.

540
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,190
Not bad at all.

541
00:37:55,680 --> 00:37:58,310
If you're seriously considering
going back out there...

542
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:00,630
«you should hear the rumors
surrounding Bane.

543
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:01,910
WAYNE:
I'm all ears.

544
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:06,410
There is a prison
in a more ancient part of the world.

545
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:11,430
A pit where men are thrown
to suffer and die.

546
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:15,319
But sometimes
a man rises from the darkness.

547
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:19,480
Sometimes the pit sends something back.

548
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:21,910
WAYNE: Bane.
-Bane.

549
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:25,000
Born and raised in hell on earth.

550
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:28,820
-Born in a prison?
-No one knows why, or how he escaped.

551
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:31,610
But they do know that once he did...

552
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:35,590
..he was trained by Ra's Al Ghul,
your mentor.

553
00:38:36,240 --> 00:38:37,919
Bane was a member
of the League of Shadows?

554
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:40,140
And then he was excommunicated.

555
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:45,650
And any man who is too extreme
for Ra's Al Ghul is not to be trifled with.

556
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:49,220
I didn't realize was known
for trifling with criminals.

557
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:51,279
That was then.

558
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:54,230
And you can strap up your leg
and put your mask back on...

559
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:56,890
..but that doesn't make you
what you were.

560
00:38:57,360 --> 00:39:01,260
If this man is everything that you say he is,
then the city needs me.

561
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:04,450
The city needs Bruce Wayne.

562
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:06,770
Your resources. Your knowledge.

563
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:09,759
It doesn't need your body, or your life.

564
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:11,860
That time's past.

565
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:15,000
You're afraid that if 1 go back out there,
I'l fail.

566
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:16,610
No.

567
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:20,710
I'm afraid that you want to.

568
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:33,210
[BELL RINGS]

569
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:34,650
[CLAMORING]

570
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:37,630
TRADER: You can't short the stock because
Bruce Wayne goes to a party.

571
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:41,390
Wayne coming back is change.
Change is either good or bad. I vote bad.

572
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,080
On what basis?

573
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:44,700
I flipped a coin.

574
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,370
It says rye-- I said no rye, man.

575
00:39:55,080 --> 00:39:57,430
Hey, rookie, lose the helmet.
We need faces for camera.

576
00:39:57,920 --> 00:39:58,790
[DEVICE BEEPING]

577
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:01,730
[TRADER CHUCKLES]

578
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,170
Come on. Let's go scalping.

579
00:40:20,200 --> 00:40:21,069
Come on.

580
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:39,180
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

581
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:46,819
MERCENARY 1:
Everybody down, now!

582
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:06,880
This is a stock exchange.
There's no money you can steal.

583
00:41:07,360 --> 00:41:10,200
BANE:
Really? Then why are you people here?

584
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,720
SECURITY CHIEF: Everybody, stay back!
Go down to the end of the block!

585
00:41:29,200 --> 00:41:30,850
We have an emergency situation!

586
00:41:34,240 --> 00:41:35,569
You gotta get in there!

587
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:37,250
This is a hostage situation.

588
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:40,480
No, this is a robbery. They have
direct access to the online trading desk.

589
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:42,550
I'm not risking my men for your money.

590
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:48,800
We have to ask you to move.
We have a situation.

591
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,959
It's not our money, it's everybody's.

592
00:41:51,360 --> 00:41:53,110
Really? Mine's in my mattress.

593
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:54,680
You don't put these guys down...

594
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:57,490
..that stuffing in your mattress
might be worth a whole lot less.

595
00:41:58,000 --> 00:41:59,890
Cut the fiber cable
and take out that cell tower.

596
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:02,420
SECURITY CHIEF: Thank you.
FOLEY: That'll slow them down.

597
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:04,230
COP:
Move back!

598
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:06,770
All the way! Go! Sir, get back, please!

599
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:09,850
They cut the fiber.

600
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:12,069
Cell's working.

601
00:42:12,360 --> 00:42:13,480
BANE:
For now.

602
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:22,170
Get all these barriers up. All of them up.
No one gets in or out of any of these streets.

603
00:42:22,760 --> 00:42:24,130
Where am I supposed to move it?

604
00:42:24,480 --> 00:42:25,560
Back it up.

605
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:31,980
All right, just stay in your vehicle, okay?

606
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:40,550
BANE: How much longer
does the program need?

607
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:43,340
Eight minutes.

608
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:46,050
BANE:
Time to go mobile.

609
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,480
MERCENARY 1:
Everybody, up!

610
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:48,780
[GUNFIRE]

611
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:52,879
You two, move!

612
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:56,840
BANE:
Thank you.

613
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,150
FOLEY:
Steady.

614
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:08,839
Steady.

615
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:17,470
SNIPER:
I've got something.

616
00:43:18,680 --> 00:43:20,779
SECURITY CHIEF:
Hold your fire, they've got hostages.

617
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:22,290
Hold your fire!

618
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:26,069
[SHRIEKS]

619
00:43:26,920 --> 00:43:27,970
[HOSTAGE 1 YELLING]

620
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,260
Go, go!

621
00:43:42,760 --> 00:43:44,160
HOSTAGE 1:
Please! Just let me go!

622
00:43:44,680 --> 00:43:46,890
Hey, please! Hey!

623
00:43:50,080 --> 00:43:51,270
Shoot the tires.

624
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:52,830
There's no shot.

625
00:43:54,360 --> 00:43:56,990
Now back off.
Back off, they've got hostages.

626
00:43:57,520 --> 00:43:59,840
MAN [ON TV]: --P.D. are pursuing
the four suspects through downtown...

627
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:02,040
..in response to a hostage situation.

628
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:09,920
What's going on with the lights?

629
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:12,790
[ELECTRICAL SYSTEMS POWER DOWN]

630
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:17,990
VETERAN COP:
It can't be.

631
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:19,509
What the hell was that?

632
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:22,190
Oh, boy, you are in
for a show tonight, son.

633
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:29,480
HOSTAGE 2:
Please! Help, help, help!

634
00:44:37,080 --> 00:44:38,410
[POWERS UP]

635
00:44:43,200 --> 00:44:44,319
[GUNSHOT]

636
00:44:46,840 --> 00:44:47,710
Sorry.

637
00:44:48,440 --> 00:44:51,210
Put that thing away
before you hurt yourself. Get in!

638
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:54,390
Let's go. You, get in the car.
They've spotted the Batman.

639
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:08,230
Call everyone in.
Every car patrol, beat cop, off-duty too.

640
00:45:08,760 --> 00:45:11,040
Pull them in now. I'm gonna do
what Jim Gordon never could.

641
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:14,220
-What's that?
-I'm gonna take down the Batman.

642
00:45:14,760 --> 00:45:17,320
MAN 1 [OVER TV]: --are confirming
four suspects are carrying two hostages...

643
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:19,560
.. kidnapped from
the Gotham Stock Exchange.

644
00:45:19,960 --> 00:45:22,730
-Reports from the eyewitnesses--
MAN 2: Scott, dead center of your screen.

645
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:25,310
MAN 1: What do you see?
MAN 2: f see Batman.

646
00:45:25,760 --> 00:45:28,010
MAN 1: Hard to believe, but the suspects
are now being pursued...

647
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:30,130
..by what appears to be the Batman.

648
00:45:30,520 --> 00:45:31,430
Well, what do you know?

649
00:45:36,520 --> 00:45:38,170
Sir, what about the armed robbers?

650
00:45:40,720 --> 00:45:43,209
HOSTAGE 1:
Please! Just let me go! Please!

651
00:45:52,840 --> 00:45:54,700
SPOTTER [OVER RADIO]:
One bike's pulled off. No hostage.

652
00:45:55,160 --> 00:45:56,029
Should we pursue?

653
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:01,820
Negative. Stay on the Batman.

654
00:46:04,800 --> 00:46:06,310
-He's getting away.
-Who do you wanna catch?

655
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:08,819
Some robber, or the son of a bitch
who killed Harvey Dent?

656
00:46:13,160 --> 00:46:15,259
MAN 1 [OVER TV]:
--the entire upper west hill...

657
00:46:15,720 --> 00:46:17,439
..Central Heights
and East Park Side areas.

658
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:20,330
DAGGETT:
Eight years, and he has to pick tonight.

659
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:22,710
He's drawing the cops off Bane.

660
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:33,090
HOSTAGE 1:
Please! Just let me go!

661
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:34,670
Please!

662
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:50,180
[MAN 1 SCREAMS]

663
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:57,190
[GROANS]

664
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:08,070
[SIRENS WAILING NEARBY]

665
00:47:49,880 --> 00:47:51,040
COP [OVER RADIO]:
We lost him.

666
00:47:51,440 --> 00:47:52,840
How could you lose him?

667
00:47:53,200 --> 00:47:54,529
COP:
He's got a lot of firepower.

668
00:47:54,880 --> 00:47:55,790
What, and you don't?

669
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:01,990
COP:
He's heading back downtown.

670
00:48:02,360 --> 00:48:04,080
Then he's as dumb as he dresses.

671
00:48:04,920 --> 00:48:06,250
Close it off, gentlemen.

672
00:48:34,040 --> 00:48:35,509
[BARKING]

673
00:48:37,440 --> 00:48:39,540
Like a rat in a trap, gentlemen.

674
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:47,430
You might have
the wrong animal there, sir.

675
00:48:58,240 --> 00:48:59,640
You sure it was him?

676
00:49:06,400 --> 00:49:09,280
STRYVER: Bane says the Batman interfered,
but the task was accomplished.

677
00:49:09,840 --> 00:49:11,210
What about the men they arrested?

678
00:49:11,560 --> 00:49:15,000
He said, and I quote,
“They would die before talking.”

679
00:49:16,640 --> 00:49:18,569
Where does he find these guys?

680
00:49:20,360 --> 00:49:21,830
Open the champagne.

681
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:26,100
And can we get some girls in here?

682
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:27,750
CATWOMAN:
Careful what you wish for.

683
00:49:38,480 --> 00:49:39,600
Cat got your tongue?

684
00:49:39,920 --> 00:49:40,930
You dumb bitch.

685
00:49:41,240 --> 00:49:42,990
Nobody ever accused me
of being dumb.

686
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:45,860
You're dumb for coming here tonight.

687
00:49:46,360 --> 00:49:47,230
[DAGGETT GROANS]

688
00:49:47,560 --> 00:49:48,960
l want what you owe me.

689
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:50,630
[GUN CLICKS]

690
00:49:50,920 --> 00:49:52,530
Want doesn't get.

691
00:49:53,240 --> 00:49:56,649
Nice outfit.
Those heels make it tough to walk?

692
00:49:57,280 --> 00:49:58,290
-I don't know.
-Aah!

693
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:00,200
Do they?

694
00:50:01,640 --> 00:50:02,970
-So where is it?
-Where's what?

695
00:50:03,360 --> 00:50:05,320
The program. The "clean slate.”

696
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:08,540
The ultimate tool for a master thief
with a record.

697
00:50:09,640 --> 00:50:10,940
BODYGUARD:
Hold it right there!

698
00:50:14,080 --> 00:50:15,660
[DAGGETT YELLS]

699
00:50:24,080 --> 00:50:24,950
Where is it?

700
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:26,930
The clean slate?

701
00:50:27,280 --> 00:50:29,490
Where you type in someone's name,
date of birth...

702
00:50:29,960 --> 00:50:33,470
..in afew minutes they're gone
from every database on earth?

703
00:50:34,480 --> 00:50:36,830
-Sound a little too good to be true?
-You're lying!

704
00:50:37,320 --> 00:50:39,490
Rykin Data took it to prototype stage.

705
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:41,610
That's why I bought them.

706
00:50:42,720 --> 00:50:44,299
But they had nothing.

707
00:50:44,920 --> 00:50:46,360
It was a gangland myth.

708
00:50:57,440 --> 00:50:58,420
CATWOMAN:
Stay back!

709
00:51:01,800 --> 00:51:03,170
I'm not bluffing!

710
00:51:04,240 --> 00:51:05,399
BATMAN:
They know.

711
00:51:05,960 --> 00:51:07,150
They just don't care.

712
00:51:23,960 --> 00:51:25,040
You've gotta be kidding me.

713
00:51:25,360 --> 00:51:27,500
-No guns. No killing.
-Where's the fun in that?

714
00:51:46,160 --> 00:51:48,509
My mother warned me about
getting into cars with strange men.

715
00:51:49,000 --> 00:51:49,870
This isn't a car.

716
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:39,410
See you around.

717
00:52:40,560 --> 00:52:41,500
You're welcome.

718
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:43,160
I had it under control.

719
00:52:43,480 --> 00:52:44,600
Those weren't street thugs.

720
00:52:44,920 --> 00:52:46,670
They were trained killers.

721
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:48,480
I saved your life.

722
00:52:48,880 --> 00:52:52,880
In return, l need to know what you did
with Bruce Wayne's fingerprints.

723
00:52:53,600 --> 00:52:55,740
Wayne wasn't kidding about
a powerful friend.

724
00:52:57,160 --> 00:52:58,740
I sold his prints to Daggett...

725
00:53:00,840 --> 00:53:02,910
..for something that doesn't even exist.

726
00:53:03,480 --> 00:53:06,600
-l doubt many people get the better of you.
-Hey, when a girl's desperate...

727
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:09,160
-What's he gonna do with them?
-I don't know...

728
00:53:09,600 --> 00:53:12,440
..but Daggett seemed pretty interested
in that mess at the stock market.

729
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:14,610
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING ABOVE]

730
00:53:17,880 --> 00:53:19,110
Miss Kyle?

731
00:53:22,080 --> 00:53:23,940
So that's what that feels like.

732
00:53:42,720 --> 00:53:46,549
I see from the television coverage that you
got your taste for wanton destruction back.

733
00:53:47,240 --> 00:53:48,890
I retrieved this.

734
00:53:49,280 --> 00:53:51,350
Aren't the police supposed
to be investigating, then?

735
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:54,680
-They don't have the tools to analyze it.
-They would if you gave them to them.

736
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:57,339
One man's tool is another man's weapon.

737
00:53:57,800 --> 00:54:00,610
In your mind, perhaps. But there aren't
many things you can't turn into a weapon.

738
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:02,950
Alfred, enough.
The police weren't getting it done.

739
00:54:03,360 --> 00:54:06,200
Perhaps they might have if you
hadn't made a sideshow of yourself.

740
00:54:06,760 --> 00:54:09,950
-You thought I didn't have it in me.
-You led a bloated police force on a chase...

741
00:54:10,560 --> 00:54:12,730
..with a load of fancy new toys from Fox.

742
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:15,589
What about when you come up
against him? What then?

743
00:54:16,080 --> 00:54:20,120
-I'll fight harder. I always have.
-Look. His speed, his ferocity, his training.

744
00:54:20,840 --> 00:54:23,090
I see the power of belief.

745
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:26,020
I see the League of Shadows resurgent.

746
00:54:26,520 --> 00:54:27,750
You said he was excommunicated.

747
00:54:28,080 --> 00:54:29,660
By Ra's Al Ghul.

748
00:54:30,880 --> 00:54:31,790
Who leads them now?

749
00:54:32,080 --> 00:54:34,250
Ra's Al Ghul was the League of Shadows
and I beat him.

750
00:54:34,720 --> 00:54:37,040
Bane is a mercenary.
We need to find out what he's up to.

751
00:54:38,520 --> 00:54:40,660
Trades of some kind. Coded.

752
00:54:41,760 --> 00:54:44,110
And my fingerprint, courtesy of Selina Kyle.

753
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:45,509
Get this to Fox.

754
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:49,450
He can crack the code and tell us
what trades they were executing.

755
00:54:53,480 --> 00:54:56,570
I'll get this to Mr. Fox, but no more.

756
00:54:58,600 --> 00:55:01,580
I've sewn you up, I've set your bones,
but I won't bury you.

757
00:55:02,400 --> 00:55:05,030
I've buried enough members
of the Wayne family.

758
00:55:06,160 --> 00:55:10,660
-You'll leave me?
-You see only one end to your journey.

759
00:55:11,720 --> 00:55:15,580
Leaving is all 1 have
to make you understand.

760
00:55:16,400 --> 00:55:19,350
You're not Batman anymore.
You have to find another way.

761
00:55:19,920 --> 00:55:23,250
You used to talk about finishing,
about a life beyond that awful cave.

762
00:55:23,880 --> 00:55:27,000
Alfred, Rachel died knowing that
we had decided to be together.

763
00:55:27,600 --> 00:55:30,860
That was my life beyond the cave.
I can't just move on.

764
00:55:31,760 --> 00:55:34,150
She-- She didn't. She couldn't.

765
00:55:35,280 --> 00:55:36,440
What if she had?

766
00:55:36,760 --> 00:55:37,990
She-- I can't change that.

767
00:55:38,320 --> 00:55:40,850
What if before she died
she wrote a letter...

768
00:55:41,360 --> 00:55:44,270
..Ssaying she chose
Harvey Dent over you?

769
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:50,000
And what if...

770
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:52,740
..to spare you pain...

771
00:55:54,720 --> 00:55:56,299
.. 1 burnt that letter?

772
00:55:57,320 --> 00:56:00,870
How dare you use Rachel to try to stop me?

773
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:04,440
lam using the truth, Master Wayne.

774
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:09,590
Maybe it's time we all stopped trying
to outsmart the truth and let it have its day.

775
00:56:11,720 --> 00:56:13,509
-I'm sorry.
-You're sorry?

776
00:56:13,920 --> 00:56:16,200
You expect to destroy my world...

777
00:56:18,800 --> 00:56:20,800
..and then think that
we're gonna shake hands?

778
00:56:21,240 --> 00:56:22,640
No, no, no.

779
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:25,790
I know what this means.

780
00:56:26,200 --> 00:56:27,109
What does it mean?

781
00:56:27,400 --> 00:56:29,430
It means your hatred.

782
00:56:29,920 --> 00:56:33,040
And it also means losing someone
that I have cared for...

783
00:56:33,640 --> 00:56:37,359
Since I first heard his cries echo...

784
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:40,270
..through this house.

785
00:56:40,840 --> 00:56:44,420
But it might also mean saving your life.

786
00:56:46,160 --> 00:56:48,190
And that is more important.

787
00:56:53,480 --> 00:56:54,350
Goodbye, Alfred.

788
00:57:03,960 --> 00:57:05,430
[DOORBELL RINGING]

789
00:57:13,440 --> 00:57:14,450
Alfred?

790
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:21,770
-Answering your own door?
-Yeah.

791
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:24,520
Page three.

792
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:28,569
Seems you made a series of large
put options on the futures exchange...

793
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:30,279
«verified by thumbprint.

794
00:57:30,600 --> 00:57:32,850
Those options expired
at midnight last night.

795
00:57:33,320 --> 00:57:37,570
Long-term, we may be able to prove fraud.
But for now, you're completely broke...

796
00:57:38,320 --> 00:57:41,200
..and Wayne Enterprises is about to fall
into the hands of John Daggett.

797
00:57:41,760 --> 00:57:44,990
The weapons. We can't let Daggett
get his hands on Applied Sciences.

798
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:48,089
Applied Sciences is all locked up
and off the books.

799
00:57:48,600 --> 00:57:51,299
The energy project, however,
is a different story.

800
00:57:51,840 --> 00:57:53,100
Miranda Tate.

801
00:57:54,240 --> 00:57:57,009
Let's convince the board to get behind her.
Let's show her the reactor.

802
00:57:57,560 --> 00:58:00,509
We're meeting her there in 35 minutes,
so you better get dressed.

803
00:58:01,240 --> 00:58:04,220
MIRANDA: You brought me out here
to show me this, Mr. Fox?

804
00:58:04,840 --> 00:58:06,490
FOX:
Bear with me, Miss Tate.

805
00:58:10,280 --> 00:58:13,190
Please keep hands and feet inside
the car at all times.

806
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:20,470
This is it, isn't it?

807
00:58:21,240 --> 00:58:23,410
The reactor is beneath the river...

808
00:58:24,240 --> 00:58:27,399
..So it can be instantly flooded
in the event of a security breach.

809
00:58:28,520 --> 00:58:30,980
Is Bruce Wayne really that paranoid?

810
00:58:31,480 --> 00:58:33,410
FOX:
I'm gonna plead the fifth on that one.

811
00:58:40,280 --> 00:58:42,740
WAYNE: I thought you might like to see
what your investment built.

812
00:58:43,240 --> 00:58:44,640
MIRANDA:
No fossil fuels.

813
00:58:45,000 --> 00:58:47,170
Free clean energy for an entire city.

814
00:58:47,640 --> 00:58:50,620
MIRANDA: Three years ago,
a Russian scientist published a paper...

815
00:58:51,200 --> 00:58:53,129
...0n weaponized fusion reactions.

816
00:58:53,560 --> 00:58:57,700
One week later, your reactor
started developing problems.

817
00:58:59,480 --> 00:59:00,850
I think this machine works.

818
00:59:01,200 --> 00:59:06,779
Miranda, if it were operational,
the danger to Gotham would be too great.

819
00:59:07,720 --> 00:59:10,319
Would it make you feel better to know
that the Russian scientist...

820
00:59:10,840 --> 00:59:13,190
..died in a plane crash six months ago?

821
00:59:13,680 --> 00:59:16,629
Someone will work out what Dr. Pavel did.

822
00:59:17,200 --> 00:59:22,399
Someone will figure out a way to make
this power source into a nuclear weapon.

823
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:28,090
I need you to take control
of Wayne Enterprises...

824
00:59:29,040 --> 00:59:30,090
..and this reactor.

825
00:59:30,640 --> 00:59:31,580
To do what with it?

826
00:59:31,880 --> 00:59:33,140
Nothing.

827
00:59:33,880 --> 00:59:35,670
Until we can guarantee its safety.

828
00:59:36,080 --> 00:59:37,090
And if we can't?

829
00:59:37,520 --> 00:59:38,820
Decommission it. Flood it.

830
00:59:39,160 --> 00:59:42,350
Destroy the world's best chance
for a sustainable future?

831
00:59:42,960 --> 00:59:44,330
If the world's not ready, yes.

832
00:59:44,680 --> 00:59:48,299
Bruce, if you want to save the world,
you have to start trusting it.

833
00:59:49,160 --> 00:59:50,319
I'm trusting you.

834
00:59:50,640 --> 00:59:52,290
Doesn't count. You have no choice.

835
00:59:53,240 --> 00:59:55,200
I could have flooded this chamber
at any time.

836
00:59:55,640 --> 00:59:57,359
I'm choosing to trust you.

837
00:59:58,440 --> 00:59:59,450
Please.

838
01:00:00,800 --> 01:00:02,830
[BOARD MEMBERS CHATTERING]

839
01:00:06,560 --> 01:00:10,000
All right, ladies and gentlemen.
This meeting will now come to order.

840
01:00:10,640 --> 01:00:13,310
DAGGETT: I'd like to point out that we have
a non-board member here...

841
01:00:13,840 --> 01:00:16,650
..which is highly irregular,
even if his family name is above the door.

842
01:00:17,200 --> 01:00:19,089
Bruce Wayne's family built this company.

843
01:00:19,520 --> 01:00:20,990
And he himself has run it.

844
01:00:21,360 --> 01:00:23,920
Into the ground, sir!
Does anybody disagree?

845
01:00:24,520 --> 01:00:25,750
Check the share price this morning.

846
01:00:26,080 --> 01:00:29,660
Crazy gambling on futures has not
only cost Mr. Wayne his seat...

847
01:00:30,320 --> 01:00:32,250
.it's cost us all a lot of money.

848
01:00:32,680 --> 01:00:34,220
And he has to go.

849
01:00:35,280 --> 01:00:36,960
I'm afraid he has a point, Mr. Wayne.

850
01:00:45,280 --> 01:00:46,680
Now, back to business.

851
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:50,259
MAN 1: Mr. Wayne, over here!
MAN 2: How's it feel to be one of the people?

852
01:00:50,800 --> 01:00:54,210
Mr. Wayne, they're towing your car!
I didn't know what to do.

853
01:00:56,360 --> 01:00:57,800
Looks like you need a ride, huh?

854
01:00:58,160 --> 01:01:00,020
MAN 3:
Wayne, we'll give you a ride!

855
01:01:00,440 --> 01:01:04,060
How the hell did Miranda Tate get
the inside track on the Wayne board?

856
01:01:04,720 --> 01:01:06,540
She been meeting with him?
Sleeping with him?

857
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:09,450
-Not that we know of.
-You don't know much of anything, do you?

858
01:01:09,960 --> 01:01:11,570
-Where's Bane?
-We told him it was urgent.

859
01:01:11,960 --> 01:01:14,170
-Where is that masked--?
BANE: Speak of the devil...

860
01:01:14,640 --> 01:01:16,529
..and he shall appear.

861
01:01:16,960 --> 01:01:19,030
What the hell is going on?

862
01:01:19,920 --> 01:01:22,760
BANE: The plan is proceeding as expected.
DAGGETT: Oh, really?

863
01:01:23,320 --> 01:01:25,670
Do I look like I'm running
Wayne Enterprises right now?

864
01:01:26,280 --> 01:01:30,110
Your hit on the stock exchange,
it didn't work, my friend.

865
01:01:30,800 --> 01:01:35,120
And now you have my construction crews
going around the city at 24 hours a day.

866
01:01:35,880 --> 01:01:40,020
How exactly is that supposed to help
my company absorb Wayne's?

867
01:01:43,080 --> 01:01:45,080
BANE: Leave us.
-No. You stay here.

868
01:01:45,520 --> 01:01:46,850
I'm in charge.

869
01:01:47,800 --> 01:01:49,800
BANE:
Do you feel in charge?

870
01:01:54,920 --> 01:01:56,390
I've paid you a small fortune.

871
01:01:56,760 --> 01:01:59,250
BANE:
And this gives you power over me?

872
01:02:00,160 --> 01:02:01,350
What is this?

873
01:02:01,680 --> 01:02:05,859
Your money and infrastructure
have been important...

874
01:02:06,800 --> 01:02:07,740
.»till now.

875
01:02:08,360 --> 01:02:09,300
What are you?

876
01:02:09,600 --> 01:02:11,140
BANE:
I'm Gotham's reckoning.

877
01:02:11,520 --> 01:02:13,940
Here to end the borrowed time
you've all been living on.

878
01:02:16,240 --> 01:02:18,870
You're pure evil.

879
01:02:19,400 --> 01:02:21,330
BANE:
I'm necessary evil.

880
01:02:21,760 --> 01:02:23,370
DAGGETT:
No. No, no, no!

881
01:02:23,760 --> 01:02:25,200
[DAGGETT SCREAMS]

882
01:02:28,000 --> 01:02:30,070
BLAKE:
When you started, why the mask?

883
01:02:30,520 --> 01:02:32,770
-To protect the people closest to me.
-But you were a loner, right?

884
01:02:33,240 --> 01:02:35,870
-You didn't have any family?
-There are always people you care about.

885
01:02:36,400 --> 01:02:39,700
You just don't realize how much
until they're gone.

886
01:02:40,560 --> 01:02:42,980
The idea was to be a symbol.

887
01:02:43,480 --> 01:02:46,110
Batman could be anybody.

888
01:02:47,000 --> 01:02:48,300
That was the point.

889
01:02:48,840 --> 01:02:51,540
-Well, it was damn good to see him back.
-Not everybody agrees.

890
01:02:52,120 --> 01:02:55,670
-They'll figure that out in the end.
-You got anything on Bane's whereabouts?

891
01:02:56,680 --> 01:02:59,379
Yeah. I got 500 pages of tunnel records
and a flashlight.

892
01:02:59,920 --> 01:03:01,670
I could use some help, actually.

893
01:03:02,880 --> 01:03:04,460
You know what? Drop me in Old Town.

894
01:03:08,160 --> 01:03:09,490
WAYNE:
Hey, hey, hey. I don't think so!

895
01:03:09,840 --> 01:03:11,660
JEN: That's the way this works!
WAYNE: I don't think so!

896
01:03:12,080 --> 01:03:13,970
-That is the way--
SELINA: He's not a mark.

897
01:03:14,400 --> 01:03:16,650
And he doesn't have a cent
to his name, anyway.

898
01:03:17,440 --> 01:03:21,060
Yeah, it's not much.
But it's more than you've got right now.

899
01:03:21,720 --> 01:03:23,750
Actually, they're letting me keep the house.

900
01:03:24,200 --> 01:03:26,370
The rich don't even go broke
the same as the rest of us, huh?

901
01:03:26,840 --> 01:03:30,170
My powerful friend might hope
to change your mind about leaving.

902
01:03:30,800 --> 01:03:33,010
-And how would he do that?
-By giving you what you want.

903
01:03:33,480 --> 01:03:35,730
-It doesn't exist.
-He says it does.

904
01:03:36,720 --> 01:03:38,160
He wants to meet tonight.

905
01:03:38,520 --> 01:03:39,390
Why?

906
01:03:39,680 --> 01:03:42,140
He needs to find Bane.
Says you'd know how.

907
01:03:45,680 --> 01:03:47,540
-Tell him I'll think about it.
-Okay.

908
01:03:47,960 --> 01:03:49,540
I like your place.

909
01:03:51,160 --> 01:03:52,100
Mr. Wayne?

910
01:03:54,760 --> 01:03:56,650
I'm sorry they took all your money.

911
01:03:57,960 --> 01:03:59,040
No, you're not.

912
01:04:00,280 --> 01:04:02,630
FOLEY: Can we help you, officer?
-Uh, yeah.

913
01:04:03,120 --> 01:04:06,100
John Daggett's body was just found
in a Dumpster about an hour ago.

914
01:04:06,680 --> 01:04:08,330
-Thought you might want to know.
-Why?

915
01:04:08,720 --> 01:04:12,200
His name's all over these permits I pulled
to, uh, map the tunnels under Gotham.

916
01:04:12,840 --> 01:04:16,100
That's MTA maintenance, uh,
sewer construction, couple of other things.

917
01:04:16,720 --> 01:04:19,250
Where did you get to
with the tunnel searches?

918
01:04:19,760 --> 01:04:22,180
Remind me to tell detail
to keep hotheads out.

919
01:04:22,680 --> 01:04:24,500
We've had teams down there.
It's a huge network.

920
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:27,730
Well, get more men. Work a grid.
1 want him found.

921
01:04:28,280 --> 01:04:30,240
Yeah, the, uh, masked man. We're on it.

922
01:04:30,680 --> 01:04:33,000
Lose the uniform,
you're working for me now.

923
01:04:33,480 --> 01:04:35,510
We could use some hotter heads
around here.

924
01:04:35,960 --> 01:04:39,440
-Sir, that could also be a coincidence.
-You're a detective now, son.

925
01:04:40,080 --> 01:04:42,710
You're not allowed to believe
in coincidence anymore.

926
01:04:44,680 --> 01:04:46,750
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

927
01:04:53,800 --> 01:04:55,100
MIRANDA:
Nobody's answering.

928
01:04:55,640 --> 01:04:56,620
No.

929
01:04:56,920 --> 01:04:58,320
I'm on my own now.

930
01:04:59,320 --> 01:05:00,510
Do you have keys?

931
01:05:01,840 --> 01:05:02,820
Never needed them.

932
01:05:09,360 --> 01:05:10,830
Hope you didn't like me for my money.

933
01:05:11,760 --> 01:05:13,930
MIRANDA:
Suffering builds character.

934
01:05:20,040 --> 01:05:22,180
I'll take care of your parents’ legacy, Bruce.

935
01:05:24,560 --> 01:05:25,680
Who's this?

936
01:05:33,360 --> 01:05:34,480
Where's Alfred?

937
01:05:36,360 --> 01:05:37,520
He left...

938
01:05:39,280 --> 01:05:40,930
..taking everything.

939
01:06:04,160 --> 01:06:05,319
What's that?

940
01:06:06,240 --> 01:06:08,169
My power's been shut off.

941
01:06:08,920 --> 01:06:10,150
[MIRANDA CHUCKLES]

942
01:06:13,720 --> 01:06:14,950
WAYNE:
You're good at that.

943
01:06:16,200 --> 01:06:18,660
When I was a child,
we had almost nothing.

944
01:06:19,440 --> 01:06:23,230
But on the nights when we had a fire,
we felt very rich indeed.

945
01:06:25,520 --> 01:06:28,009
l assumed your family was wealthy.

946
01:06:29,120 --> 01:06:30,380
Not always.

947
01:06:31,520 --> 01:06:32,820
Not when I was young.

948
01:06:33,640 --> 01:06:35,180
An old mistake.

949
01:06:36,480 --> 01:06:38,060
I've made a few myself.

950
01:06:39,480 --> 01:06:40,850
More than a few.

951
01:06:43,200 --> 01:06:44,460
We could leave.

952
01:06:45,120 --> 01:06:45,990
Tonight.

953
01:06:46,960 --> 01:06:50,370
Take my plane, go anywhere we wanted.

954
01:06:52,560 --> 01:06:54,070
Someday, perhaps.

955
01:06:55,200 --> 01:06:56,430
Not tonight.

956
01:07:23,640 --> 01:07:25,180
Don't be shy.

957
01:07:27,480 --> 01:07:29,510
Wayne says you can get me
the clean slate.

958
01:07:30,120 --> 01:07:32,440
-That depends.
-On what?

959
01:07:32,920 --> 01:07:34,290
On what you want it for.

960
01:07:34,640 --> 01:07:37,100
l acquired it to keep it out
of the wrong hands.

961
01:07:38,200 --> 01:07:39,669
Still don't trust me, huh?

962
01:07:40,960 --> 01:07:42,680
How can we change that?

963
01:07:43,080 --> 01:07:44,590
Start by taking me to Bane.

964
01:07:47,720 --> 01:07:49,049
You asked.

965
01:07:51,440 --> 01:07:53,160
From here,
Bane's men patrol the tunnels.

966
01:07:53,720 --> 01:07:55,790
And they're not your average brawlers.

967
01:07:56,560 --> 01:07:57,820
BATMAN:
Neither am I.

968
01:08:05,480 --> 01:08:06,390
-He's behind you.
-Who?

969
01:08:06,680 --> 01:08:07,549
BATMAN:
Me.

970
01:08:12,640 --> 01:08:14,290
MERCENARY 1:
What do you think you're--?

971
01:08:26,160 --> 01:08:28,019
CATWOMAN:
Just a little further.

972
01:08:35,200 --> 01:08:37,340
l had to find a way to stop them
trying to kill me.

973
01:08:37,800 --> 01:08:39,830
You made a serious mistake.

974
01:08:40,680 --> 01:08:44,820
BANE:
Not as serious as yours, I fear.

975
01:08:48,920 --> 01:08:49,790
Bane.

976
01:08:50,080 --> 01:08:52,680
BANE:
Let's not stand on ceremony here...

977
01:08:54,240 --> 01:08:56,200
...Mr. Wayne.

978
01:09:07,240 --> 01:09:09,059
Peace has cost you your strength.

979
01:09:09,479 --> 01:09:11,019
Victory has defeated you.

980
01:09:18,439 --> 01:09:20,189
[BATMAN GRUNTING]

981
01:09:57,720 --> 01:09:58,950
[BATMAN YELLS]

982
01:10:10,480 --> 01:10:15,219
BANE: Theatricality and deception,
powerful agents to the uninitiated.

983
01:10:16,040 --> 01:10:18,390
But we are initiated, aren't we, Bruce?

984
01:10:19,600 --> 01:10:21,990
Members of the League of Shadows.

985
01:10:24,240 --> 01:10:26,240
And you betrayed us.

986
01:10:27,320 --> 01:10:29,780
BATMAN:
“Us"? You were excommunicated...

987
01:10:30,280 --> 01:10:32,420
..by a gang of psychopaths.

988
01:10:37,000 --> 01:10:39,460
BANE:
lam the League of Shadows.

989
01:10:39,960 --> 01:10:42,590
And I'm here to fulfill
Ra's Al Ghul's destiny.

990
01:10:55,960 --> 01:10:57,710
You fight like a younger man.

991
01:10:58,120 --> 01:11:00,050
Nothing held back.

992
01:11:00,480 --> 01:11:03,179
Admirable, but mistaken.

993
01:11:06,840 --> 01:11:10,700
Oh, you think darkness is your ally?

994
01:11:11,400 --> 01:11:13,679
But you merely adopted the dark.

995
01:11:14,640 --> 01:11:16,360
I was born in it.

996
01:11:17,160 --> 01:11:18,950
Molded by it.

997
01:11:20,320 --> 01:11:22,920
I didn't see the light
until l was already a man.

998
01:11:23,440 --> 01:11:26,179
By then, it was nothing to me
but blinding!

999
01:11:29,440 --> 01:11:32,769
The shadows betray you
because they belong to me!

1000
01:11:38,400 --> 01:11:41,099
I will show you where
I have made my home...

1001
01:11:41,640 --> 01:11:44,450
..whilst preparing to bring justice.

1002
01:11:46,960 --> 01:11:48,820
Then I will break you.

1003
01:11:57,480 --> 01:11:59,059
Your precious armory.

1004
01:11:59,920 --> 01:12:02,730
Gratefully accepted. We will need it.

1005
01:12:11,480 --> 01:12:14,669
Ah, yes. was wondering
what would break first.

1006
01:12:15,280 --> 01:12:16,540
[BATMAN YELLS]

1007
01:12:19,680 --> 01:12:21,190
Your spirit...

1008
01:12:25,640 --> 01:12:27,080
..or your body.

1009
01:13:09,480 --> 01:13:12,110
Get me Commissioner Gordon. I got a line
on the congressman's kidnapping.

1010
01:13:25,040 --> 01:13:26,019
-Excuse me, miss.
-Uh, yes?

1011
01:13:26,320 --> 01:13:28,990
I'm gonna need to see your ticket
and identification, please.

1012
01:13:29,520 --> 01:13:31,240
Oh. Do you mind?

1013
01:13:43,760 --> 01:13:46,390
I showed your picture to
the congressman. Guess what.

1014
01:13:47,040 --> 01:13:49,180
Don't tell me. Still in love?

1015
01:13:49,640 --> 01:13:51,780
Oh, head over heels.
Pressing charges, though.

1016
01:13:53,080 --> 01:13:55,500
You've made some mistakes, Ms. Kyle.

1017
01:13:56,760 --> 01:13:59,430
-Girl's gotta eat.
-And you have an appetite.

1018
01:14:00,120 --> 01:14:02,010
Why would you run?
You can't hide with a record like this.

1019
01:14:02,440 --> 01:14:04,160
Maybe it's not you I'm running from.

1020
01:14:04,560 --> 01:14:06,140
Who then? Bane?

1021
01:14:06,520 --> 01:14:07,750
What do you know about him?

1022
01:14:08,920 --> 01:14:11,830
That you should be as afraid of him
as lam.

1023
01:14:12,400 --> 01:14:13,980
We can offer you protection.

1024
01:14:17,360 --> 01:14:18,230
Okay.

1025
01:14:22,840 --> 01:14:25,790
When I spotted you, I was looking
for a friend of mine. Bruce Wayne.

1026
01:14:28,960 --> 01:14:30,220
Did they kill him?

1027
01:14:32,080 --> 01:14:33,450
I'm not sure.

1028
01:14:45,160 --> 01:14:46,070
[GASPS]

1029
01:14:52,640 --> 01:14:54,010
Why didn't you just...

1030
01:14:56,120 --> 01:14:57,099
Kill me?

1031
01:14:57,400 --> 01:15:00,309
BANE:
You don't fear death, you welcome it.

1032
01:15:01,240 --> 01:15:03,559
Your punishment must be more severe.

1033
01:15:04,600 --> 01:15:05,930
Torture?

1034
01:15:06,440 --> 01:15:07,349
Yes.

1035
01:15:08,400 --> 01:15:09,980
But not of your body.

1036
01:15:13,720 --> 01:15:14,950
Of your soul.

1037
01:15:16,520 --> 01:15:17,460
Where am I?

1038
01:15:18,120 --> 01:15:18,990
BANE:
Home.

1039
01:15:20,040 --> 01:15:22,500
Where I learned the truth about despair.

1040
01:15:23,800 --> 01:15:24,920
As will you.

1041
01:15:25,680 --> 01:15:28,700
There is a reason why this prison
is the worst hell on earth:

1042
01:15:29,880 --> 01:15:31,040
Hope.

1043
01:15:31,360 --> 01:15:33,990
Every man who has rotted here
over the centuries...

1044
01:15:34,520 --> 01:15:37,400
..has looked up to the light
and imagined climbing to freedom.

1045
01:15:38,840 --> 01:15:39,960
So easy.

1046
01:15:41,000 --> 01:15:42,050
So simple.

1047
01:15:43,120 --> 01:15:47,830
And like shipwrecked men turning
to seawater from uncontrollable thirst...

1048
01:15:50,480 --> 01:15:52,129
..many have died trying.

1049
01:15:53,200 --> 01:15:56,320
I learned here there can be
no true despair without hope.

1050
01:15:58,560 --> 01:16:00,810
So as I terrorize Gotham...

1051
01:16:01,280 --> 01:16:04,610
..1 will feed its people hope
to poison their souls.

1052
01:16:05,480 --> 01:16:07,620
I will let them believe
that they can survive...

1053
01:16:08,080 --> 01:16:13,100
..So that you can watch them clambering
over each other to stay in the sun.

1054
01:16:16,520 --> 01:16:19,150
You can watch me torture an entire city.

1055
01:16:20,160 --> 01:16:23,210
And then when you have truly understood
the depth of your failure...

1056
01:16:23,920 --> 01:16:26,410
..we will fulfill Ra's Al Ghul's destiny.

1057
01:16:30,280 --> 01:16:31,889
We will destroy Gotham.

1058
01:16:33,360 --> 01:16:35,429
And then, when it is done...

1059
01:16:36,160 --> 01:16:37,530
..and Gotham is...

1060
01:16:39,480 --> 01:16:40,639
«ashes...

1061
01:16:46,240 --> 01:16:48,559
..then you have my permission to die.

1062
01:16:50,520 --> 01:16:51,920
[YELLS]

1063
01:16:53,400 --> 01:16:54,940
[GROANS]

1064
01:17:01,200 --> 01:17:02,280
[MEN CHEERING AND WHOOPING]

1065
01:17:02,600 --> 01:17:03,860
GUARD:
You're locking her up in here?

1066
01:17:04,200 --> 01:17:07,429
The Dent Act allows non-segregation
based on extraordinary need.

1067
01:17:08,040 --> 01:17:10,640
First time she broke out
of women's correctional, she was 16.

1068
01:17:11,160 --> 01:17:12,139
INMATE:
Little closer, baby.

1069
01:17:12,440 --> 01:17:14,160
Why, honey? You wanna hold my hand?

1070
01:17:14,560 --> 01:17:15,430
[INMATE YELLS]

1071
01:17:15,720 --> 01:17:16,520
She's gonna be fine.

1072
01:17:18,800 --> 01:17:20,970
FOX: I still don't see the need
of a board meeting.

1073
01:17:21,440 --> 01:17:22,769
MIRANDA:
Bruce got a lot of things right.

1074
01:17:23,120 --> 01:17:25,220
Keeping the board in the dark
was not one of them.

1075
01:17:28,000 --> 01:17:29,230
BANE:
How good of you to join us.

1076
01:17:30,080 --> 01:17:32,290
Chair. President.

1077
01:17:32,760 --> 01:17:35,850
All l need now is one more
ordinary board member.

1078
01:17:36,440 --> 01:17:39,320
Mr. Fox, would you like to nominate?

1079
01:17:39,880 --> 01:17:40,930
FREDERICKS:
No.

1080
01:17:41,240 --> 01:17:42,500
I will volunteer.

1081
01:17:43,080 --> 01:17:44,480
FOX:
Where are you taking us?

1082
01:17:46,800 --> 01:17:48,450
[DRILLING]

1083
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:57,270
You were right, commissioner.
Will you excuse us, please?

1084
01:17:57,920 --> 01:17:58,790
What happened?

1085
01:17:59,080 --> 01:18:00,870
Your masked man kidnapped
the Wayne Enterprises board.

1086
01:18:01,280 --> 01:18:03,740
He let most of them go,
but he took three into the sewers.

1087
01:18:04,240 --> 01:18:06,200
No more patrols. No more hide and seek.

1088
01:18:06,640 --> 01:18:08,920
Get every available cop down there
and smoke him out!

1089
01:18:09,400 --> 01:18:10,700
The mayor won't want panic.

1090
01:18:11,040 --> 01:18:12,860
So it's a training exercise.

1091
01:18:15,440 --> 01:18:17,469
I'm sorry I didn't take you seriously.

1092
01:18:18,520 --> 01:18:19,390
GORDON:
Not you.

1093
01:18:19,680 --> 01:18:21,680
You're telling me the Batman's gone...

1094
01:18:22,120 --> 01:18:26,090
..So you chase up the Daggett leads
any way you can.

1095
01:18:26,960 --> 01:18:27,830
Yes, sir.

1096
01:18:34,320 --> 01:18:36,000
[MAN SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1097
01:18:37,960 --> 01:18:42,560
He asks how much you would pay us
to let you die.

1098
01:18:43,360 --> 01:18:45,040
I told him. I told him you have nothing.

1099
01:18:46,000 --> 01:18:47,050
Do it for the pleasure.

1100
01:18:47,680 --> 01:18:50,170
They pay me more than that
to keep you alive.

1101
01:18:54,400 --> 01:18:56,750
[PRISONERS CHANTING]

1102
01:18:58,000 --> 01:18:59,540
He will try the climb.

1103
01:19:00,280 --> 01:19:02,139
[GROANS]

1104
01:19:13,640 --> 01:19:15,710
WAYNE:
Has anyone ever made it?

1105
01:19:16,880 --> 01:19:18,110
Of course not.

1106
01:19:19,160 --> 01:19:20,320
[YELLS]

1107
01:19:26,320 --> 01:19:27,440
[SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1108
01:19:28,360 --> 01:19:30,360
He says there is one who did.

1109
01:19:31,520 --> 01:19:32,850
Achild.

1110
01:19:34,240 --> 01:19:35,960
A child born in this hell.

1111
01:19:37,080 --> 01:19:38,410
Bane.

1112
01:19:38,800 --> 01:19:41,400
An old legend. Nothing more.

1113
01:19:45,400 --> 01:19:46,379
WAYNE:
Don't.

1114
01:19:46,680 --> 01:19:50,370
Whatever it is they want you to see,
it's happening soon.

1115
01:20:15,480 --> 01:20:16,950
MERCENARY:
Fire in the hole!

1116
01:20:20,720 --> 01:20:22,260
[EXPLOSION NEARBY]

1117
01:20:44,720 --> 01:20:45,980
BANE:
Turn it on.

1118
01:20:49,720 --> 01:20:53,790
l only need one other board member.
There are eight others waiting.

1119
01:20:54,520 --> 01:20:55,750
I won't do it.

1120
01:20:56,400 --> 01:20:57,269
MIRANDA:
All right, stop.

1121
01:20:58,880 --> 01:21:01,340
Lucius, you'll kill this man,
and yourself...

1122
01:21:01,840 --> 01:21:03,350
«and you'll barely slow them down.

1123
01:21:09,360 --> 01:21:10,440
[MACHINE BEEPS]

1124
01:21:23,800 --> 01:21:25,480
[MACHINE POWERS UP]

1125
01:21:29,080 --> 01:21:30,940
BANE:
Go on, then. Do your work.

1126
01:21:34,080 --> 01:21:35,870
Take them up to the surface.

1127
01:21:36,280 --> 01:21:37,860
People of their status...

1128
01:21:38,240 --> 01:21:42,660
..deserve to experience
the next era of western civilization.

1129
01:21:47,120 --> 01:21:50,599
BLAKE: I've been to Daggett's cement plants
and locations they poured underground.

1130
01:21:51,240 --> 01:21:53,240
GORDON [OVER PHONE]:
Anything strange about the pourings?

1131
01:21:54,040 --> 01:21:56,920
Honestly, commissioner, I don't know
anything about civil engineering.

1132
01:21:57,480 --> 01:21:59,940
But you know about patterns.
Keep looking.

1133
01:22:05,480 --> 01:22:06,419
PAVEL:
It's done.

1134
01:22:06,720 --> 01:22:10,370
This is now a 4-megaton nuclear bomb.

1135
01:22:12,080 --> 01:22:14,400
BANE:
Pull the core out of the reactor.

1136
01:22:16,200 --> 01:22:17,780
PAVEL:
No, you cannot.

1137
01:22:18,320 --> 01:22:21,410
This is the only power source
capable of sustaining it.

1138
01:22:22,240 --> 01:22:25,469
If you move it,
the core will decay in a matter of months.

1139
01:22:26,080 --> 01:22:27,900
BANE:
Five, by my calculations.

1140
01:22:28,320 --> 01:22:29,719
And then it will go off!

1141
01:22:31,640 --> 01:22:34,970
BANE: And for the sake of your children,
Dr. Pavel...

1142
01:22:35,600 --> 01:22:37,490
..indeed I hope it does.

1143
01:22:38,400 --> 01:22:40,650
Hey. Hey!

1144
01:22:42,840 --> 01:22:45,470
That was you in front
of the stock exchange, wasn't it?

1145
01:22:46,440 --> 01:22:47,839
-When?
-When?

1146
01:22:48,200 --> 01:22:51,820
When cops were trying to pull onto Castle
Street and your truck was shutting them out.

1147
01:22:52,480 --> 01:22:55,459
-Oh, yeah. You're the cop.
-Detective now.

1148
01:22:56,040 --> 01:22:59,410
And, uh, as a detective, we're not
allowed to believe in coincidence.

1149
01:23:09,240 --> 01:23:11,769
What were you doing here?
What are you working on?

1150
01:23:19,320 --> 01:23:20,620
Commissioner, it's Blake.

1151
01:23:20,960 --> 01:23:24,790
I got two dead witnesses
and a lot of questions. Call me whenev--

1152
01:23:25,720 --> 01:23:28,530
Wait a minute. I'm looking at
four barrels of polyisobutylene.

1153
01:23:30,640 --> 01:23:32,530
That looks like motor oil right next to it.

1154
01:23:32,960 --> 01:23:35,660
Jesus, they're not making cement.
They're making explosives.

1155
01:23:43,440 --> 01:23:45,759
-Patch me in to Foley.
DISPATCH: Foley's overseeing the operation.

1156
01:23:46,240 --> 01:23:47,360
They're heading into a trap!

1157
01:23:48,720 --> 01:23:50,930
REPORTER: We're seeing thousands
of police heading into the sewers.

1158
01:23:51,400 --> 01:23:54,309
-Mr. Mayor? Literally thousands.
-It's a training exercise, that's all.

1159
01:23:54,880 --> 01:23:58,290
Now if you'll excuse me, I've got tickets
to watch our boys thrash Rapid City.

1160
01:24:00,600 --> 01:24:02,280
-Foley.
BLAKE: It's a trap! Pull everyone out!

1161
01:24:02,680 --> 01:24:03,980
Bane has been pouring concrete...

1162
01:24:04,320 --> 01:24:05,969
-..laced with explosives!
-Where?

1163
01:24:08,360 --> 01:24:14,679
[SINGING] Oh, say, can you see
By the dawn's early light

1164
01:24:16,400 --> 01:24:21,179
What so proudly we hailed
At the twilight's....

1165
01:24:22,160 --> 01:24:25,320
BLAKE: There's a ring around the tunnels!
They'll blow it and trap the cops!

1166
01:24:26,800 --> 01:24:29,190
Pull them out. Pull them out now!

1167
01:24:29,680 --> 01:24:33,120
SINGER:
Through the perilous fight

1168
01:24:34,080 --> 01:24:37,269
O'er the ramparts we watched

1169
01:24:38,240 --> 01:24:41,650
Were so gallantly streaming

1170
01:24:42,560 --> 01:24:45,720
And the rockets' red glare

1171
01:24:46,800 --> 01:24:49,960
The bombs bursting in air

1172
01:24:50,920 --> 01:24:52,360
Gave proof through--

1173
01:24:52,760 --> 01:24:54,580
BANE:
That's a lovely, lovely voice.

1174
01:24:55,000 --> 01:24:58,480
--that our flag was still there

1175
01:24:59,720 --> 01:25:07,170
Oh, say does that star-spangled banner
Yet wave

1176
01:25:09,520 --> 01:25:13,770
O'er the land of the free

1177
01:25:15,240 --> 01:25:20,370
And the home of the brave

1178
01:25:26,680 --> 01:25:28,610
[CHEERING]

1179
01:25:30,480 --> 01:25:31,490
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1180
01:25:33,960 --> 01:25:35,470
BANE:
Let the games begin.

1181
01:25:39,080 --> 01:25:40,940
[RUMBLING]

1182
01:25:52,560 --> 01:25:54,070
[OFFICERS YELLING]

1183
01:26:04,320 --> 01:26:05,969
[CROWD SCREAMING]

1184
01:26:49,000 --> 01:26:50,610
COP 1:
Everybody okay?

1185
01:26:51,640 --> 01:26:53,180
COP 2: Let's move! Move, move!
COP 3: Go, go!

1186
01:27:06,840 --> 01:27:08,100
BANE:
Gotham...

1187
01:27:10,000 --> 01:27:11,820
..take control.

1188
01:27:12,800 --> 01:27:15,680
Take control of your city.

1189
01:27:21,080 --> 01:27:22,660
-Foley.
-Jesus, Blake.

1190
01:27:23,040 --> 01:27:24,650
Every cop in the city's in those tunnels.

1191
01:27:25,920 --> 01:27:27,080
Not every cop.

1192
01:27:29,240 --> 01:27:31,059
[MEDICAL DEVICE BEEPING]

1193
01:27:40,720 --> 01:27:43,320
Sir, are you okay? I'm a police officer.
I need your car right now.

1194
01:27:48,640 --> 01:27:50,080
[HORN HONKING]

1195
01:28:21,800 --> 01:28:23,310
[GUNSHOTS NEARBY]

1196
01:28:32,720 --> 01:28:34,400
Clear the corners, rookie.

1197
01:28:35,720 --> 01:28:36,770
Get my coat, son.

1198
01:28:37,080 --> 01:28:38,550
BANE:
This....

1199
01:28:39,680 --> 01:28:42,210
This is the instrument of your liberation.

1200
01:28:45,120 --> 01:28:47,510
ANALYST:
Satellite shows a radiation spike.

1201
01:28:48,640 --> 01:28:50,570
Whatever it is, it's nuclear.

1202
01:28:55,120 --> 01:28:57,860
BANE:
Identify yourself to the world.

1203
01:28:59,520 --> 01:29:03,240
Dr. Leonid Pavel, nuclear physicist.

1204
01:29:04,120 --> 01:29:06,080
Pavel was confirmed dead.

1205
01:29:06,520 --> 01:29:09,500
Plane crash on an agency pull
out of Uzbekistan, but....

1206
01:29:10,880 --> 01:29:11,820
It looks like it's him.

1207
01:29:12,240 --> 01:29:14,980
BANE:
And what...? What is this?

1208
01:29:15,520 --> 01:29:18,780
It's a fully primed neutron bomb...

1209
01:29:19,400 --> 01:29:21,400
..With a blast radius of six miles.

1210
01:29:22,480 --> 01:29:25,320
BANE: And who is capable of disarming
such a device?

1211
01:29:27,720 --> 01:29:28,800
Only me.

1212
01:29:29,680 --> 01:29:31,050
BANE:
Only you.

1213
01:29:32,200 --> 01:29:34,130
Thank you, good doctor!

1214
01:29:34,880 --> 01:29:36,320
[CROWD SCREAMS]

1215
01:29:36,880 --> 01:29:39,650
Now, this bomb is armed!

1216
01:29:40,200 --> 01:29:42,370
And this bomb is mobile!

1217
01:29:42,840 --> 01:29:46,670
And the identity of the triggerman
is a mystery.

1218
01:29:47,720 --> 01:29:51,790
For one of you holds the detonator!

1219
01:29:52,520 --> 01:29:55,360
Now, we come here
not as conquerors...

1220
01:29:55,920 --> 01:30:00,630
..but as liberators, to return control
of this city to the people.

1221
01:30:02,440 --> 01:30:06,410
And at the first sign of interference
from the outside world...

1222
01:30:07,640 --> 01:30:10,830
..Or from those people
attempting to flee...

1223
01:30:13,120 --> 01:30:15,330
..this anonymous Gothamite...

1224
01:30:15,800 --> 01:30:19,910
..this unsung hero, will trigger the bomb.

1225
01:30:22,800 --> 01:30:24,800
For now, martial law is in effect.

1226
01:30:25,760 --> 01:30:29,800
Return to your homes,
hold your families close...

1227
01:30:31,600 --> 01:30:32,790
and wait.

1228
01:30:34,040 --> 01:30:36,600
Tomorrow, you claim
what is rightfully yours.

1229
01:30:43,000 --> 01:30:44,370
GENERAL:
Pull back the fighters.

1230
01:30:45,360 --> 01:30:47,530
Start high-level reconnaissance flights.

1231
01:30:48,760 --> 01:30:50,270
Get the president on the line.

1232
01:31:10,160 --> 01:31:14,059
MERCENARY 1: Tanks and planes
cannot stop us from detonating our device.

1233
01:31:15,040 --> 01:31:19,500
Send an emissary to discuss terms
of access for supplies and communication.

1234
01:31:24,800 --> 01:31:26,550
CAPTAIN:
How many of you are there, son?

1235
01:31:28,360 --> 01:31:31,549
You don't have enough men to stop
12 million people from leaving this island.

1236
01:31:32,760 --> 01:31:34,790
No. No, we don't.

1237
01:31:35,240 --> 01:31:36,110
But you do.

1238
01:31:36,440 --> 01:31:37,599
[CHUCKLES]

1239
01:31:37,920 --> 01:31:40,660
Now, why the hell would I try
to help you keep your hostages?

1240
01:31:41,200 --> 01:31:43,730
If one person crosses this bridge...

1241
01:31:44,240 --> 01:31:45,750
..Gotham gets blown to hell.

1242
01:31:51,640 --> 01:31:53,990
The people of our greatest city are resilient.

1243
01:31:55,360 --> 01:31:58,339
They have proven this before,
and they will prove it again.

1244
01:32:00,640 --> 01:32:03,170
We do not negotiate with terrorists...

1245
01:32:04,360 --> 01:32:05,900
..but we do recognize realities.

1246
01:32:07,160 --> 01:32:08,950
As this situation develops...

1247
01:32:09,680 --> 01:32:12,350
..one thing must be understood
above aif others.

1248
01:32:14,800 --> 01:32:17,260
People of Gotham,
we have not abandoned you.

1249
01:32:17,760 --> 01:32:18,880
What does that mean?

1250
01:32:19,640 --> 01:32:21,570
It means we're on our own.

1251
01:32:22,320 --> 01:32:23,759
I have to get in front of a camera.

1252
01:32:24,400 --> 01:32:26,290
They will kill you the second
you show your face.

1253
01:32:27,280 --> 01:32:30,540
Bane says he's giving Gotham back to the
people. They need to know I could lead.

1254
01:32:31,160 --> 01:32:32,490
Bane's not gonna let that happen.

1255
01:32:32,840 --> 01:32:34,140
Then he'll show his true colors.

1256
01:32:34,480 --> 01:32:35,849
And you'll be dead.

1257
01:32:53,920 --> 01:32:58,200
BANE:
Behind you stands a symbol of oppression.

1258
01:32:59,400 --> 01:33:00,629
Blackgate Prison...

1259
01:33:00,960 --> 01:33:03,980
..where a thousand men have languished...

1260
01:33:04,560 --> 01:33:07,510
..under the name of this man:

1261
01:33:08,080 --> 01:33:09,830
Harvey Dent.

1262
01:33:10,800 --> 01:33:12,970
Who has been held up to you...

1263
01:33:13,440 --> 01:33:17,230
as the shining example of justice!

1264
01:33:17,920 --> 01:33:20,450
We're just gonna keep moving you
till we can get you in front of the camera.

1265
01:33:20,960 --> 01:33:24,290
BANE: You have been supplied
with a false idol to stop you...

1266
01:33:24,920 --> 01:33:26,950
..tearing down this corrupt city!

1267
01:33:27,400 --> 01:33:28,769
Yes! Yes! Yes!

1268
01:33:29,120 --> 01:33:32,170
BANE:
Let me tell you the truth about Harvey Dent.

1269
01:33:32,760 --> 01:33:36,830
From the words of Gotham's
police commissioner...

1270
01:33:37,560 --> 01:33:39,560
-.James Gordon:

1271
01:33:40,400 --> 01:33:43,210
“The Batman didn't murder Harvey Dent.

1272
01:33:43,760 --> 01:33:45,370
He saved my boy...

1273
01:33:45,800 --> 01:33:49,520
then took the blame
for Harvey's appalling crimes...

1274
01:33:50,200 --> 01:33:52,410
..So that I could, to my shame...

1275
01:33:52,880 --> 01:33:55,930
.- build a lie around this...

1276
01:33:56,520 --> 01:33:58,800
.fallen idol.

1277
01:34:01,320 --> 01:34:05,460
1 praised the madman
who tried to murder my own child.

1278
01:34:06,240 --> 01:34:09,400
Well, l can no longer live with my lie.

1279
01:34:10,000 --> 01:34:13,160
It is time to trust the people of Gotham
with the truth...

1280
01:34:13,760 --> 01:34:17,200
.and it is time for me to resign."

1281
01:34:18,600 --> 01:34:21,410
And do you accept this man's resignation?

1282
01:34:21,960 --> 01:34:23,120
[INMATES YELLING]

1283
01:34:23,520 --> 01:34:27,070
And do you accept the resignation
of all of these liars?

1284
01:34:27,720 --> 01:34:29,120
Of all the corrupt?

1285
01:34:32,960 --> 01:34:34,850
BLAKE: Those men locked up
for eight years in Blackgate...

1286
01:34:35,280 --> 01:34:38,860
..and denied parole under the Dent Act,
it was based on a lie.

1287
01:34:40,360 --> 01:34:41,730
Gotham needed a hero.

1288
01:34:42,080 --> 01:34:45,630
Well, it needs it now more than ever,
but you betrayed everything you stood for.

1289
01:34:47,960 --> 01:34:52,740
There's a point far out there
when the structures fail you...

1290
01:34:53,560 --> 01:34:55,980
..when the rules aren't weapons anymore...

1291
01:34:57,000 --> 01:34:59,910
..they're shackles,
letting the bad guy get ahead.

1292
01:35:01,920 --> 01:35:04,800
One day, you may face...

1293
01:35:05,360 --> 01:35:06,759
«such a moment of crisis.

1294
01:35:07,120 --> 01:35:09,890
And in that moment,
I hope you have a friend like I did...

1295
01:35:10,920 --> 01:35:15,270
..to plunge their hands into the filth,
so that you can keep yours clean!

1296
01:35:17,360 --> 01:35:19,610
Your hands look plenty filthy to me,
soe
commissioner.

1297
01:35:21,480 --> 01:35:24,429
BANE:
We take Gotham from the corrupt!

1298
01:35:27,040 --> 01:35:27,950
The rich!

1299
01:35:28,960 --> 01:35:30,610
The oppressors of generations...

1300
01:35:31,000 --> 01:35:34,510
..who have kept you down
with myths of opportunity.

1301
01:35:35,160 --> 01:35:37,720
And we give it back to you...

1302
01:35:38,680 --> 01:35:40,540
..the people.

1303
01:35:41,840 --> 01:35:43,450
Gotham is yours!

1304
01:35:44,120 --> 01:35:46,930
None shall interfere. Do as you please.

1305
01:35:49,480 --> 01:35:52,429
But start by storming Blackgate
and freeing the oppressed!

1306
01:35:53,000 --> 01:35:54,440
MAN:
Open it!

1307
01:36:02,240 --> 01:36:04,800
BANE:
Step forward, those who would serve...

1308
01:36:06,680 --> 01:36:08,150
..for an army will be raised.

1309
01:36:12,440 --> 01:36:16,299
The powerful will be ripped
from their decadent nests...

1310
01:36:21,360 --> 01:36:26,000
..and cast out into the cold world
that we know and endure!

1311
01:36:31,040 --> 01:36:32,790
Courts will be convened.

1312
01:36:40,400 --> 01:36:42,330
Spoils will be enjoyed.

1313
01:36:47,200 --> 01:36:48,570
Blood will be shed!

1314
01:36:51,960 --> 01:36:54,210
The police will survive...

1315
01:36:54,680 --> 01:36:58,400
as they learn to serve true justice.

1316
01:37:00,000 --> 01:37:02,100
This great city...

1317
01:37:04,480 --> 01:37:05,740
.»it will endure.

1318
01:37:08,520 --> 01:37:11,680
Gotham will survive!

1319
01:37:15,480 --> 01:37:17,759
[GROANING]

1320
01:37:25,760 --> 01:37:26,700
[GRUNTING]

1321
01:37:29,480 --> 01:37:32,459
[BLIND PRISONER
SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1322
01:37:33,040 --> 01:37:35,070
He says you must first fix your back.

1323
01:37:35,600 --> 01:37:36,540
WAYNE:
How does he know?

1324
01:37:36,840 --> 01:37:38,030
PRISONER:
He was the prison doctor.

1325
01:37:38,360 --> 01:37:41,620
He's a morphine addict
who incurred the displeasure...

1326
01:37:42,240 --> 01:37:45,540
..Of powerful people,
including your masked friend.

1327
01:37:46,880 --> 01:37:48,140
How?

1328
01:37:49,520 --> 01:37:53,140
Many years ago, it was a time of plague.

1329
01:37:55,160 --> 01:37:57,760
Some of the other prisoners attacked Bane.

1330
01:38:00,080 --> 01:38:03,170
The doctor's fumbling attempts
to repair the damage...

1331
01:38:04,360 --> 01:38:05,730
..left him in perpetual agony.

1332
01:38:06,080 --> 01:38:08,750
The mask holds the pain at bay.

1333
01:38:09,280 --> 01:38:12,090
Bane was the child you spoke of?

1334
01:38:12,640 --> 01:38:13,720
He was born here?

1335
01:38:14,800 --> 01:38:18,560
The legend is that there was a mercenary
who worked for a local warlord.

1336
01:38:19,800 --> 01:38:21,760
He fell in love with
the warlord's daughter.

1337
01:38:22,520 --> 01:38:23,850
They were married in secret.

1338
01:38:24,200 --> 01:38:25,880
When the warlord found out...

1339
01:38:26,600 --> 01:38:29,830
..the mercenary was condemned to this pit.

1340
01:38:30,840 --> 01:38:32,730
But then he exiled him instead.

1341
01:38:33,160 --> 01:38:36,570
The mercenary understood that it was
the daughter who had secured his release.

1342
01:38:37,200 --> 01:38:41,309
But what he could not know
was the true price of his freedom.

1343
01:38:42,880 --> 01:38:44,390
She took his place in the pit.

1344
01:38:47,600 --> 01:38:48,900
And she was with child...

1345
01:38:49,240 --> 01:38:50,849
.the mercenary's child.

1346
01:38:53,560 --> 01:38:56,260
Innocence cannot flower underground.
It has to be stamped out.

1347
01:38:59,160 --> 01:39:04,180
One day, the doctor forgot
to lock the cell.

1348
01:39:11,360 --> 01:39:13,320
But the child had a friend...

1349
01:39:14,040 --> 01:39:18,640
..a protector who showed the others
that this innocence was their redemption.

1350
01:39:19,440 --> 01:39:20,879
it was to be prized.

1351
01:39:21,240 --> 01:39:22,710
The mother was not so lucky.

1352
01:39:23,480 --> 01:39:24,950
[SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1353
01:39:25,960 --> 01:39:29,050
This is Bane's prison now.
He wouldn't want this story told.

1354
01:39:31,920 --> 01:39:33,640
[YELLING]

1355
01:39:40,400 --> 01:39:43,519
There's a vertebra protruding
from your back.

1356
01:39:44,320 --> 01:39:46,070
It has to be put back.

1357
01:39:47,080 --> 01:39:48,730
[YELLS]

1358
01:39:51,120 --> 01:39:53,470
Stay like this until you stand.

1359
01:40:00,800 --> 01:40:05,540
RA'S AL GHUL: Tsk, tsk, tsk. Did you not
think I would return, Bruce? Hmm?

1360
01:40:06,840 --> 01:40:08,210
[RA'S AL GHUL CHUCKLES]

1361
01:40:11,640 --> 01:40:13,010
I told you I was immortal.

1362
01:40:15,640 --> 01:40:17,430
l watched-- I watched you die.

1363
01:40:17,840 --> 01:40:20,330
Oh, there are many forms of immortality.

1364
01:40:22,520 --> 01:40:23,750
Once, I had a wife...

1365
01:40:25,400 --> 01:40:26,839
..my great love.

1366
01:40:28,360 --> 01:40:31,200
-She was taken from me.
-You were the mercenary.

1367
01:40:35,480 --> 01:40:37,129
Bane is your child.

1368
01:40:38,920 --> 01:40:39,790
Your heir.

1369
01:40:40,080 --> 01:40:42,400
An heir to ensure
the League of Shadows fulfills its duty...

1370
01:40:42,880 --> 01:40:45,090
..to restore balance to civilization.

1371
01:40:45,560 --> 01:40:46,430
No.

1372
01:40:46,720 --> 01:40:49,600
You yourself fought the decadence
of Gotham for years...

1373
01:40:50,160 --> 01:40:51,769
with all your strength...

1374
01:40:52,360 --> 01:40:55,910
all your resources,
all your moral authority.

1375
01:40:57,120 --> 01:40:59,650
And the only victory you could
achieve was a lie.

1376
01:41:00,600 --> 01:41:03,020
Now you understand.
Gotham is beyond saving.

1377
01:41:03,520 --> 01:41:04,460
No.

1378
01:41:04,760 --> 01:41:06,550
-And must be allowed to die.
-No!

1379
01:41:13,440 --> 01:41:15,120
PRISONER:
Yeah, just lift your head.

1380
01:41:15,760 --> 01:41:16,950
Oh, that's good.

1381
01:41:22,720 --> 01:41:23,590
No, no!

1382
01:41:57,640 --> 01:41:59,600
JEN: What's that?
SELINA: This was someone's home.

1383
01:42:00,040 --> 01:42:01,650
JEN:
And now it's everyone's home.

1384
01:42:03,600 --> 01:42:06,160
There's a storm coming, remember?
This is what you wanted.

1385
01:42:29,920 --> 01:42:31,780
[CHATTERING]

1386
01:42:34,440 --> 01:42:36,790
It's for the bus,
in case there's a chance to evacuate.

1387
01:42:37,280 --> 01:42:38,580
Any news? Is the commissioner--?

1388
01:42:38,920 --> 01:42:41,730
The less you know, Father.
How are the boys doing?

1389
01:42:42,280 --> 01:42:44,630
REILLY: Well, we've had more power on,
so they've got some TV.

1390
01:42:45,120 --> 01:42:46,240
It's good to see you.

1391
01:42:47,080 --> 01:42:50,490
Blake, you be careful out there.
They're hunting down cops like dogs.

1392
01:42:56,440 --> 01:42:57,519
Why build yourself?

1393
01:42:59,920 --> 01:43:04,100
WAYNE: I'm not meant to die in here.
-Here, there. What's the difference?

1394
01:43:11,600 --> 01:43:13,600
[PRISONERS CHANTING]

1395
01:43:47,760 --> 01:43:49,200
[YELLS]

1396
01:44:03,880 --> 01:44:06,690
I told you it could not be done.

1397
01:44:07,240 --> 01:44:08,610
You told me a child did it.

1398
01:44:08,960 --> 01:44:09,830
[CHUCKLES]

1399
01:44:10,120 --> 01:44:12,050
But no ordinary child.

1400
01:44:12,480 --> 01:44:14,830
A child born in hell.

1401
01:44:19,320 --> 01:44:20,549
Forged from suffering.

1402
01:44:22,760 --> 01:44:24,690
Hardened by pain.

1403
01:44:26,440 --> 01:44:28,650
Not a man from privilege.

1404
01:44:47,240 --> 01:44:48,889
ANALYST:
We got boots on the ground, sir.

1405
01:44:49,880 --> 01:44:50,790
Just waiting on intel.

1406
01:44:56,400 --> 01:44:57,269
You have ID?

1407
01:44:58,080 --> 01:44:58,950
Of course not.

1408
01:44:59,240 --> 01:45:01,380
-Well, how can we trust you?
GORDON: We don't have any choice.

1409
01:45:02,520 --> 01:45:04,480
Commissioner Gordon.
Captain Jones, Special Forces.

1410
01:45:04,920 --> 01:45:06,220
Captain. Glad to have you here.

1411
01:45:06,560 --> 01:45:08,810
It's our job, sir.
Now, uh, how many of you are there?

1412
01:45:09,280 --> 01:45:11,740
Well, there's dozens.
I'd rather not say exactly.

1413
01:45:12,240 --> 01:45:14,980
But the men trapped underground
number almost 3000.

1414
01:45:15,520 --> 01:45:17,130
JONES: Condition?
GORDON: Getting food and water.

1415
01:45:17,520 --> 01:45:19,450
JONES: Can we break them out?
BLAKE: Yes, sir.

1416
01:45:19,880 --> 01:45:21,840
Take out the mercenaries
south of Ackerman Park.

1417
01:45:22,280 --> 01:45:24,559
Blow the rubble, make a hole
big enough for 10 at a time.

1418
01:45:25,040 --> 01:45:27,740
I'm in contact with my partner
who's down there. They're just waiting.

1419
01:45:28,280 --> 01:45:29,889
Men who haven't seen daylight
in months?

1420
01:45:30,280 --> 01:45:32,099
Officers who haven't seen daylight
in months.

1421
01:45:32,520 --> 01:45:34,770
What about the bomb?
Satellite can't pick up radiation hot spots.

1422
01:45:35,600 --> 01:45:38,440
GORDON: They keep it on a truck.
it must have a lead-lined roof.

1423
01:45:39,000 --> 01:45:41,250
-They move it constantly.
JONES: Good. So you know the truck?

1424
01:45:41,720 --> 01:45:44,530
GORDON: Well, it's one of three.
We've been tracking it.

1425
01:45:45,280 --> 01:45:46,150
Decoy.

1426
01:45:47,760 --> 01:45:50,640
-You don't really think he's coming back?
-Doesn't matter what I think.

1427
01:45:51,200 --> 01:45:54,460
Actually, it does. You should put your faith
in something a little more real.

1428
01:45:55,080 --> 01:45:57,780
GORDON: The routes don't vary much.
JONES: Okay. What about the triggerman?

1429
01:45:58,320 --> 01:46:01,730
No leads. It's a bluff. Bane wouldn't give
control of that bomb to someone else.

1430
01:46:02,360 --> 01:46:05,910
We can't take that chance. Until we have
the triggerman, we just track the device.

1431
01:46:06,560 --> 01:46:09,860
And meanwhile, Gotham lives under
a warlord, like some failed state?

1432
01:46:10,480 --> 01:46:12,900
Dial it back, officer.
This situation is unprecedented.

1433
01:46:13,400 --> 01:46:17,820
-We can't do risk millions of lives.
-You gonna tell him what's really going on?

1434
01:46:18,600 --> 01:46:21,200
Captain, the situation is more
complicated than you think.

1435
01:46:21,720 --> 01:46:23,580
There's someone you need to meet.

1436
01:46:24,160 --> 01:46:27,420
Came upstairs looking for a vantage point.
Found the people who run the corporation.

1437
01:46:28,040 --> 01:46:29,019
What corporation?

1438
01:46:29,320 --> 01:46:31,320
Wayne Enterprises. You good?

1439
01:46:40,280 --> 01:46:42,099
Mr. Fox, would you like to brief
the captain?

1440
01:46:42,560 --> 01:46:44,730
Miss Tate's fully aware of the situation.

1441
01:46:45,200 --> 01:46:48,960
And as CEO of Wayne Enterprises,
I have to take responsibility for it.

1442
01:46:49,640 --> 01:46:51,320
-Why?
-We built it.

1443
01:46:51,720 --> 01:46:52,980
You built the bomb?

1444
01:46:53,320 --> 01:46:56,830
It was built as a fusion reactor.
First of its kind.

1445
01:46:57,480 --> 01:47:00,320
Bane turned the core into a bomb
and removed it from the reactor.

1446
01:47:00,880 --> 01:47:03,720
-Here's the important part.
-As the device's fuel cells deteriorate...

1447
01:47:04,280 --> 01:47:05,889
..it becomes increasingly unstable...

1448
01:47:06,280 --> 01:47:07,580
..to the point of detonation.

1449
01:47:07,920 --> 01:47:09,390
This bomb is a time bomb.

1450
01:47:09,760 --> 01:47:13,130
And it will go off in 23 days,
regardless of Bane's revolution...

1451
01:47:13,760 --> 01:47:16,040
..or what we, or the outside world,
choose to do.

1452
01:47:16,520 --> 01:47:18,690
So your plan might not be
as practical as you thought.

1453
01:47:19,520 --> 01:47:20,390
Could you disarm it?

1454
01:47:20,680 --> 01:47:23,420
I could reconnect it to the reactor. Stabilize it.

1455
01:47:23,960 --> 01:47:26,590
-Let's move from this location and call it in.
-Right. Let's go.

1456
01:47:27,120 --> 01:47:29,820
No, no, we'll take it from here.
You stay and look after these folks.

1457
01:47:32,720 --> 01:47:34,160
[GUNFIRE]

1458
01:47:34,520 --> 01:47:35,750
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

1459
01:47:37,240 --> 01:47:38,290
Someone sold us out.

1460
01:47:40,000 --> 01:47:41,230
Go, go, go!

1461
01:48:01,840 --> 01:48:03,590
I'll die before I talk.

1462
01:48:04,520 --> 01:48:06,410
BANE:
I'm on your schedule, captain.

1463
01:48:06,840 --> 01:48:08,210
[GRUNTS]

1464
01:48:12,880 --> 01:48:14,840
MERCENARY:
There were people living upstairs.

1465
01:48:15,600 --> 01:48:17,390
BANE:
Round them up for judgment...

1466
01:48:21,320 --> 01:48:25,429
..and hang them where the world can see.

1467
01:48:27,960 --> 01:48:32,000
REPORTER: Police have cordoned off
Central Heights and East Park Side areas...

1468
01:48:32,720 --> 01:48:36,160
-.as well as Merchant and South Shoreline
Boulevards in an attempt--

1469
01:48:38,080 --> 01:48:39,730
[BLIND PRISONER SPEAKS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1470
01:48:40,120 --> 01:48:43,530
He says the leap to freedom
is not about strength.

1471
01:48:44,440 --> 01:48:46,089
My body makes the jump.

1472
01:48:46,800 --> 01:48:50,060
[IN ENGLISH]
Survival is the spirit. The soul.

1473
01:48:53,320 --> 01:48:55,809
My soul is as ready to escape as my body.

1474
01:48:56,320 --> 01:48:58,849
Fear is why you fail.

1475
01:48:59,480 --> 01:49:00,780
No, I'm not afraid.

1476
01:49:02,560 --> 01:49:03,820
I'm angry.

1477
01:49:06,440 --> 01:49:08,089
[PRISONERS CHANTING]

1478
01:49:23,720 --> 01:49:25,050
[GRUNTS]

1479
01:49:32,040 --> 01:49:33,269
THOMAS:
Bruce.

1480
01:49:34,600 --> 01:49:35,510
Why do we fall?

1481
01:49:35,960 --> 01:49:37,570
[GASPS]

1482
01:49:41,440 --> 01:49:43,019
BLIND PRISONER:
You do not fear death.

1483
01:49:44,240 --> 01:49:48,070
You think this makes you strong.
It makes you weak.

1484
01:49:49,120 --> 01:49:49,990
Why?

1485
01:49:50,280 --> 01:49:52,170
How can you move faster than possible...

1486
01:49:52,720 --> 01:49:54,790
.. fight longer than possible...

1487
01:49:55,360 --> 01:49:58,380
.. without the most powerful impulse
of the spirit?

1488
01:50:00,000 --> 01:50:01,370
The fear of death.

1489
01:50:02,240 --> 01:50:03,820
I do fear death.

1490
01:50:05,760 --> 01:50:07,410
I fear dying in here...

1491
01:50:08,400 --> 01:50:10,009
..while my city burns.

1492
01:50:11,240 --> 01:50:12,849
There's no one there to save it.

1493
01:50:14,400 --> 01:50:15,660
Then make the climb.

1494
01:50:16,000 --> 01:50:17,470
[CHUCKLES]

1495
01:50:20,680 --> 01:50:21,800
How?

1496
01:50:23,400 --> 01:50:24,910
As the child did...

1497
01:50:29,640 --> 01:50:31,040
.. without the rope.

1498
01:50:33,800 --> 01:50:35,730
Then fear will find you again.

1499
01:50:42,720 --> 01:50:44,610
Ah, supplies for your journey?

1500
01:50:45,040 --> 01:50:46,790
Oh, that's wonderful. That's....

1501
01:50:49,440 --> 01:50:50,910
[PRISONERS CHANTING]

1502
01:50:51,400 --> 01:50:52,769
What does that mean?

1503
01:50:53,480 --> 01:50:54,530
Rise.

1504
01:50:55,960 --> 01:50:56,830
No.

1505
01:51:16,760 --> 01:51:18,160
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1506
01:51:55,240 --> 01:51:56,920
[CHEERING]

1507
01:52:23,240 --> 01:52:24,849
No, there's been a mistake!

1508
01:52:25,240 --> 01:52:26,920
Take me to Bane!

1509
01:52:29,640 --> 01:52:31,040
I want to see Bane!

1510
01:52:34,360 --> 01:52:35,269
CRANE:
Order!

1511
01:52:35,560 --> 01:52:37,880
This is a mistake! Where is Bane?

1512
01:52:38,360 --> 01:52:40,150
CRANE:
There's been no mistake, Mr. Stryver.

1513
01:52:40,760 --> 01:52:42,790
You are Philip Stryver...

1514
01:52:43,240 --> 01:52:46,190
executive vice president
of Daggett Industries...

1515
01:52:46,760 --> 01:52:49,810
..who for years has been living off
the blood and sweat...

1516
01:52:50,400 --> 01:52:52,259
..Of people less powerful than him.

1517
01:52:52,680 --> 01:52:55,280
Call Bane. lam one of you.

1518
01:52:55,880 --> 01:52:58,860
CRANE: Bane has no authority here.
This is merely a sentencing hearing.

1519
01:52:59,440 --> 01:53:01,230
Now, the choice is yours.

1520
01:53:01,640 --> 01:53:03,670
Exile or death!

1521
01:53:04,640 --> 01:53:05,970
[ALL SHOUTING AND CHEERING]

1522
01:53:08,400 --> 01:53:09,589
CRANE:
Order!

1523
01:53:10,320 --> 01:53:11,400
Exi-- Exile.

1524
01:53:12,280 --> 01:53:13,469
Sold.

1525
01:53:13,800 --> 01:53:15,270
To the man in the cold sweat.

1526
01:53:22,560 --> 01:53:23,750
You follow the thick ice.

1527
01:53:24,080 --> 01:53:25,870
You try to swim, you're dead in minutes.

1528
01:53:26,280 --> 01:53:27,610
Has anyone made it?

1529
01:53:40,680 --> 01:53:42,710
GORDON: Where are they?
it's not like we have a lot of time.

1530
01:53:43,440 --> 01:53:44,379
VETERAN COP:
How long?

1531
01:53:44,680 --> 01:53:46,220
The bomb goes off tomorrow.

1532
01:53:46,840 --> 01:53:49,370
-We have about 18 hours to do something.
-To do what?

1533
01:53:49,880 --> 01:53:53,250
GORDON: To mark the truck. Get GPS on it
so we can figure out how to bring it down.

1534
01:54:00,160 --> 01:54:01,210
That's it?

1535
01:54:03,760 --> 01:54:04,670
Foley.

1536
01:54:06,280 --> 01:54:09,580
-Where's Foley, damn it?
-You shouldn't be out on the streets.

1537
01:54:14,560 --> 01:54:17,020
-Jim, he's not here.
-You let your wife come to the door?

1538
01:54:17,520 --> 01:54:20,080
-When the city’s under occupation?
-Wait in the kitchen, honey.

1539
01:54:20,600 --> 01:54:22,810
What did you do,
bury your uniform in the backyard?

1540
01:54:23,280 --> 01:54:25,070
You saw what they did
to those Special Forces.

1541
01:54:25,480 --> 01:54:27,440
Have you forgotten all the years
we were out on patrol?

1542
01:54:27,880 --> 01:54:30,510
When every gangbanger wanted to plant
one as soon as our backs were turned?

1543
01:54:31,040 --> 01:54:34,519
That was different. These guys run the city.
The government's done a deal with them.

1544
01:54:35,160 --> 01:54:37,300
Bane's got their balls in a vice.
That's not a deal.

1545
01:54:37,760 --> 01:54:40,530
You move on Bane,
the triggerman is gonna hit the button.

1546
01:54:41,080 --> 01:54:44,410
You think he's given control of that bomb
to one of the people?

1547
01:54:45,040 --> 01:54:46,720
You think this is part of some revolution?

1548
01:54:47,120 --> 01:54:49,510
There's one man with his finger
on the button. That's Bane.

1549
01:54:50,000 --> 01:54:52,600
Look, we've all got to keep our heads
down till they can fix this.

1550
01:54:53,120 --> 01:54:56,170
-If you still had a family here--
-This only gets fixed from inside...

1551
01:54:56,760 --> 01:54:58,090
..the city!

1552
01:54:58,600 --> 01:55:00,000
Look, Peter.

1553
01:55:01,120 --> 01:55:03,720
I'm not asking you to walk down Grand
in your dress blues...

1554
01:55:04,240 --> 01:55:05,360
..but something has to be done.

1555
01:55:05,680 --> 01:55:07,400
-Sorry, Jim. I gotta--
-Keep your head down?

1556
01:55:07,800 --> 01:55:09,620
What good's that gonna do
when that thing blows?

1557
01:55:10,040 --> 01:55:12,110
You don't know that's gonna happen.

1558
01:55:14,240 --> 01:55:15,610
[DOOR LOCKS]

1559
01:55:16,400 --> 01:55:18,330
MIRANDA: I hear you're looking for men,
soe
commissioner.

1560
01:55:18,760 --> 01:55:19,810
How about me instead?

1561
01:55:20,120 --> 01:55:22,290
Miss Tate, I, uh, can't ask you to do that.

1562
01:55:23,520 --> 01:55:24,390
Please.

1563
01:55:26,040 --> 01:55:27,860
GANGBANGER:
You little punk! What'd you take?

1564
01:55:28,280 --> 01:55:30,210
KID:
Nothing! I didn't take anything!

1565
01:55:30,640 --> 01:55:33,410
You steal from us, you little bastard?

1566
01:55:34,360 --> 01:55:37,730
Now, you boys know you can't come into
my neighborhood without asking politely.

1567
01:55:43,880 --> 01:55:46,620
Never steal anything from someone
you can't outrun, kid.

1568
01:55:53,400 --> 01:55:55,120
WAYNE:
You're pretty generous for a thief.

1569
01:56:03,680 --> 01:56:06,000
-I thought they killed you.
-Not yet.

1570
01:56:06,640 --> 01:56:09,310
-If you're expecting an apology, I--
-It wouldn't suit you.

1571
01:56:11,040 --> 01:56:11,910
I need your help.

1572
01:56:12,560 --> 01:56:13,790
And why would I help you?

1573
01:56:14,120 --> 01:56:15,800
For this. Clean slate.

1574
01:56:16,200 --> 01:56:17,880
You'd trust me with that?

1575
01:56:18,680 --> 01:56:20,050
After what I did to you?

1576
01:56:20,400 --> 01:56:22,860
I'll admit, I was a little let down.

1577
01:56:24,760 --> 01:56:27,390
But I still think there's more to you.
In fact, I think that for you...

1578
01:56:28,160 --> 01:56:29,280
..this isn't just a tool.

1579
01:56:29,600 --> 01:56:32,300
It's an escape route.
You want to disappear. Start fresh.

1580
01:56:33,560 --> 01:56:36,050
-I can't even get off this island.
-l can give you a way off...

1581
01:56:36,560 --> 01:56:37,860
..once you get me to Lucius Fox.

1582
01:56:38,200 --> 01:56:40,550
Find out where they're holding him
and take me in.

1583
01:56:44,480 --> 01:56:45,389
Why do you need Fox?

1584
01:56:45,680 --> 01:56:47,780
-To save the city.
-Who says it needs saving?

1585
01:56:48,240 --> 01:56:49,570
Maybe I like it this way.

1586
01:56:49,920 --> 01:56:51,290
Maybe you do...

1587
01:56:52,800 --> 01:56:54,760
..but tomorrow that bomb's going off.

1588
01:56:57,520 --> 01:56:58,960
Got your powerful friend on the case?

1589
01:56:59,320 --> 01:57:00,440
I'm trying...

1590
01:57:01,400 --> 01:57:02,769
..but I need Fox.

1591
01:57:03,120 --> 01:57:04,590
As it approaches...

1592
01:57:05,560 --> 01:57:06,540
flip the switch.

1593
01:57:06,840 --> 01:57:09,820
The needle hits 200, you give me the signal,
I'll mark the truck. Okay?

1594
01:57:11,560 --> 01:57:12,930
Heads up, heads up.

1595
01:57:28,560 --> 01:57:30,490
-I got it.
-Mercenaries on your 6.

1596
01:57:30,920 --> 01:57:33,550
MERCENARY: Stand still! Keep your hands
where we can see them!

1597
01:57:36,040 --> 01:57:37,760
Commissioner Gordon,
you are under arrest.

1598
01:57:38,160 --> 01:57:39,599
GORDON:
On whose authority?

1599
01:57:39,960 --> 01:57:40,970
The people of Gotham.

1600
01:57:42,080 --> 01:57:46,220
No lawyer? No witnesses?
What sort of due process is this?

1601
01:57:46,960 --> 01:57:49,660
CRANE: Your guilt has been determined,
this is merely a sentencing hearing.

1602
01:57:50,440 --> 01:57:51,769
Now, what will it be?

1603
01:57:53,120 --> 01:57:55,400
Death or exile?

1604
01:57:55,880 --> 01:57:59,880
Crane, if you think we're going out
onto that ice willingly...

1605
01:58:00,600 --> 01:58:01,930
..you have another thing coming.

1606
01:58:04,520 --> 01:58:05,640
Death, then.

1607
01:58:05,960 --> 01:58:07,820
-Looks that way.
CRANE: Very well.

1608
01:58:08,240 --> 01:58:09,500
Death...

1609
01:58:10,960 --> 01:58:12,400
«by exile.

1610
01:58:12,760 --> 01:58:14,200
[ALL SHOUTING]

1611
01:58:15,080 --> 01:58:16,309
BANE:
Bring her to me.

1612
01:58:22,720 --> 01:58:26,270
ROSS: Hey, we're going now.
Blake says they're ready! Get your gear on!

1613
01:58:26,920 --> 01:58:29,480
Hey, you hear me?
We're going now. Let's do it.

1614
01:58:33,800 --> 01:58:35,690
MERCENARY 1: Find this one a spot,
got a big day tomorrow.

1615
01:58:36,120 --> 01:58:38,790
MERCENARY 2: We all do.
It's not every day you bag Bruce Wayne.

1616
01:58:41,320 --> 01:58:42,480
-Bruce.
WAYNE: You okay?

1617
01:58:42,800 --> 01:58:44,800
Picked a hell of a time to go on vacation,
Mr. Wayne.

1618
01:58:45,240 --> 01:58:46,639
How long until that core ignites?

1619
01:58:47,000 --> 01:58:50,230
-That bomb goes off in 12 hours.
-Unless we can reconnect it to the reactor.

1620
01:58:51,400 --> 01:58:54,030
-Can you get Miranda out of here?
-Not tonight. I'm sorry.

1621
01:58:55,160 --> 01:58:57,050
-Do what's necessary.
WAYNE: Tonight I need you.

1622
01:58:57,480 --> 01:58:59,509
FOX: What for?
-To get me back in the game.

1623
01:58:59,960 --> 01:59:03,470
Sorry to spoil things, boys,
but Bane wants these guys to himself.

1624
01:59:06,200 --> 01:59:08,800
-l won't forget about you, Miranda.
-I know.

1625
01:59:18,080 --> 01:59:19,590
I like your girlfriend, Mr. Wayne.

1626
01:59:19,960 --> 01:59:21,500
He should be so lucky.

1627
01:59:27,240 --> 01:59:29,559
Any move I make on Bane or the bomb...

1628
01:59:30,040 --> 01:59:31,620
..the triggerman sets it off.

1629
01:59:32,000 --> 01:59:34,350
FOX: Well, they won't use radio or cell.
Too much interference.

1630
01:59:34,840 --> 01:59:36,240
Infrared doesn't have the range.

1631
01:59:36,600 --> 01:59:38,920
It'll have to be a microburst. Longwave.

1632
01:59:39,400 --> 01:59:40,910
-Could you block it?
-Yes.

1633
01:59:41,280 --> 01:59:44,330
But I'll need the EMP cannon
guidance mount from the Bat.

1634
01:59:45,880 --> 01:59:47,250
Remember where you parked?

1635
02:00:01,240 --> 02:00:02,469
She fly okay?

1636
02:00:03,640 --> 02:00:05,920
Yeah, even without the autopilot.

1637
02:00:06,400 --> 02:00:08,889
-Thanks.
-Autopilot? That's what you're there for.

1638
02:00:47,360 --> 02:00:49,710
ROSS: Okay. It's clear. Come on, quick.
One at a time.

1639
02:00:52,400 --> 02:00:53,309
[GUNSHOT]

1640
02:00:53,800 --> 02:00:54,920
COP 1:
Wait, wait!

1641
02:00:56,360 --> 02:00:57,589
COP 2:
Ross!

1642
02:00:57,920 --> 02:00:59,080
COP 3:
Ross?

1643
02:00:59,840 --> 02:01:01,590
-Lock it up.
COP 3: No, keep down.

1644
02:01:02,480 --> 02:01:03,809
COP 4:
Get down!

1645
02:01:05,560 --> 02:01:06,610
Who are you?

1646
02:01:34,960 --> 02:01:36,040
BATMAN:
Light it up.

1647
02:01:53,440 --> 02:01:56,110
BOY: Dad, check it out.
MRS. FOLEY: Honey, come take a look.

1648
02:02:06,440 --> 02:02:07,879
BANE:
Impossible.

1649
02:02:08,840 --> 02:02:10,310
Keep her close.

1650
02:02:11,160 --> 02:02:12,559
He'll come for her.

1651
02:02:13,080 --> 02:02:14,550
BATMAN:
Where's Miranda Tate?

1652
02:02:15,400 --> 02:02:16,629
Bane took her.

1653
02:02:17,000 --> 02:02:19,770
He's holed up at city hall,
surrounded by his army.

1654
02:02:20,440 --> 02:02:22,540
This blocks the remote detonator signal
to the bomb.

1655
02:02:23,000 --> 02:02:26,090
Get it onto it before sunrise.
They might hit the button when it starts.

1656
02:02:27,400 --> 02:02:28,379
When what starts?

1657
02:02:29,000 --> 02:02:30,010
War.

1658
02:02:43,400 --> 02:02:44,379
[GUN COCKS]

1659
02:03:04,560 --> 02:03:05,500
You missed a spot.

1660
02:03:09,080 --> 02:03:11,360
If you're working alone, wear a mask.

1661
02:03:11,920 --> 02:03:13,530
I'm not afraid to be seen
standing up to them.

1662
02:03:13,920 --> 02:03:16,620
The mask is not for you.
It's to protect the people you care about.

1663
02:03:18,640 --> 02:03:20,290
Count to five, then throw.

1664
02:03:20,680 --> 02:03:22,260
[DEVICE BEEPING]

1665
02:03:30,480 --> 02:03:32,730
No offense, but you got
something bigger in that belt?

1666
02:03:43,040 --> 02:03:45,670
-What now?
-All-out assault on Bane.

1667
02:03:46,200 --> 02:03:48,090
But you need to get people
across the bridge.

1668
02:03:48,520 --> 02:03:50,410
-Why?
-In case we fail.

1669
02:03:50,840 --> 02:03:53,120
Lead an exodus.
Save as many lives as you can.

1670
02:03:53,600 --> 02:03:54,680
You don't need me here?

1671
02:03:55,000 --> 02:03:56,300
You've given me an army.

1672
02:03:56,640 --> 02:03:57,620
Now go.

1673
02:03:58,480 --> 02:03:59,389
Hey, thanks.

1674
02:03:59,680 --> 02:04:00,800
Don't thank me yet.

1675
02:04:01,120 --> 02:04:02,840
Well, l might not get a chance later.

1676
02:04:16,360 --> 02:04:17,799
You shouldn't have.

1677
02:04:18,920 --> 02:04:20,740
BATMAN: The midtown tunnel's
blocked by debris...

1678
02:04:21,160 --> 02:04:24,000
..but the cannons have enough firepower
to make a path for people.

1679
02:04:24,560 --> 02:04:26,100
Wait until the fighting begins.

1680
02:04:26,480 --> 02:04:28,759
You're gonna wage a war
to save your stuck-up girlfriend?

1681
02:04:29,240 --> 02:04:30,110
To start it, throttle--

1682
02:04:30,400 --> 02:04:31,629
[ENGINE REVS]

1683
02:04:31,960 --> 02:04:34,630
-I got it.
-We have 45 minutes to save this city.

1684
02:04:35,160 --> 02:04:37,480
No, I've got 45 minutes to get clear
of the blast radius.

1685
02:04:37,960 --> 02:04:40,730
-You don't stand a chance.
-With your help, I might.

1686
02:04:41,280 --> 02:04:43,280
I'll open that tunnel, then I'm gone.

1687
02:04:44,600 --> 02:04:45,930
There's more to you than that.

1688
02:04:49,640 --> 02:04:51,390
Sorry to keep letting you down.

1689
02:04:55,160 --> 02:04:56,460
Come with me.

1690
02:04:57,880 --> 02:04:59,210
Save yourself.

1691
02:05:01,560 --> 02:05:03,840
You don't owe these people any more.

1692
02:05:04,320 --> 02:05:06,110
You've given them everything.

1693
02:05:06,520 --> 02:05:07,750
Not everything.

1694
02:05:08,320 --> 02:05:09,370
Not yet.

1695
02:05:47,920 --> 02:05:49,320
MERCENARY [OVER BULLHORN]:
Disperse!

1696
02:05:49,680 --> 02:05:51,540
Disperse or be fired upon!

1697
02:05:53,160 --> 02:05:55,160
There's only one police in this town.

1698
02:05:56,080 --> 02:05:57,660
[MERCENARIES CLAMORING]

1699
02:06:32,840 --> 02:06:34,240
BANE:
Open fire.

1700
02:06:43,480 --> 02:06:45,440
[COPS CHEER]

1701
02:07:23,560 --> 02:07:25,000
-Here it comes!
-Get ready!

1702
02:07:53,840 --> 02:07:57,280
BANE:
So you came back to die with your city.

1703
02:07:58,080 --> 02:08:01,269
No. I came back to stop you.

1704
02:08:12,320 --> 02:08:13,190
Now!

1705
02:08:25,720 --> 02:08:27,090
That's impossible.

1706
02:08:29,080 --> 02:08:30,450
Cut over to Fifth!

1707
02:08:44,120 --> 02:08:45,800
Here you go. Get on the bus. Go ahead.

1708
02:08:46,200 --> 02:08:48,370
You, come with me. You too.

1709
02:08:48,880 --> 02:08:51,440
Hey, you, you, and you,
come here, come here.

1710
02:08:51,960 --> 02:08:53,500
Everyone else get on the bus, okay?

1711
02:08:53,880 --> 02:08:56,130
You guys, you go knock on doors
and spread the word, okay?

1712
02:08:56,600 --> 02:08:59,860
The bomb is gonna go off. Get out by
the South Street tunnel or over the bridge.

1713
02:09:00,480 --> 02:09:02,759
You do two blocks and you get back
to the bus, all right?

1714
02:09:03,240 --> 02:09:04,820
Go, go, go!

1715
02:09:05,200 --> 02:09:06,360
Is he back?

1716
02:09:07,840 --> 02:09:08,960
Keep your eyes open. Go, go.

1717
02:09:50,400 --> 02:09:52,610
[MASK HISSES & BANE GROANS]

1718
02:10:10,800 --> 02:10:12,060
[BANE YELLING]

1719
02:10:28,360 --> 02:10:29,660
BATMAN:
Cover the doors!

1720
02:10:32,880 --> 02:10:34,180
Where's your trigger?!

1721
02:10:34,680 --> 02:10:36,050
Where is it?!

1722
02:10:37,120 --> 02:10:39,510
You'd never give it
to an ordinary citizen!

1723
02:10:40,000 --> 02:10:42,210
Where is it? Where's your trigger?

1724
02:10:42,680 --> 02:10:43,550
[MASK HISSING]

1725
02:10:43,840 --> 02:10:46,120
Where is it?! Where is it?!

1726
02:10:53,920 --> 02:10:55,710
Tell me where the trigger is.

1727
02:10:56,440 --> 02:10:59,460
Then you have my permission to die.

1728
02:11:11,520 --> 02:11:12,960
BANE:
I broke you.

1729
02:11:14,400 --> 02:11:15,980
How have you come back?

1730
02:11:16,360 --> 02:11:20,150
You think you're the only one who could
learn the strength to escape?

1731
02:11:20,840 --> 02:11:21,920
Where's the trigger?

1732
02:11:22,720 --> 02:11:24,680
BANE:
But I never escaped.

1733
02:11:25,800 --> 02:11:27,100
But the child.

1734
02:11:29,000 --> 02:11:30,720
The child of Ra's Al Ghul made the climb.

1735
02:11:31,120 --> 02:11:33,120
MIRANDA:
But he's not the child of Ra's Al Ghul.

1736
02:11:33,560 --> 02:11:35,560
[BATMAN GRUNTS]

1737
02:11:37,160 --> 02:11:38,280
lam.

1738
02:11:38,880 --> 02:11:40,910
And though I'm not ordinary...

1739
02:11:42,480 --> 02:11:43,919
[am a citizen.

1740
02:12:02,920 --> 02:12:03,900
BATMAN:
Miranda?

1741
02:12:06,800 --> 02:12:07,670
Why?

1742
02:12:08,520 --> 02:12:09,640
Talia.

1743
02:12:10,600 --> 02:12:13,160
My mother named me Talia,
before she was killed...

1744
02:12:14,320 --> 02:12:17,200
..the way I would have been killed,
if not for my protector...

1745
02:12:18,040 --> 02:12:18,910
..Bane.

1746
02:12:26,680 --> 02:12:27,660
Goodbye.

1747
02:12:29,960 --> 02:12:31,750
TALIA:
I climbed out of the pit.

1748
02:12:37,720 --> 02:12:39,230
1 found my father...

1749
02:12:42,280 --> 02:12:44,910
..and brought him back
to exact terrible vengeance.

1750
02:12:46,120 --> 02:12:47,590
But by that time...

1751
02:12:48,880 --> 02:12:52,040
..the prisoners and doctor had done
their work to my friend.

1752
02:12:52,640 --> 02:12:53,650
My protector.

1753
02:12:57,640 --> 02:12:58,900
The League took us in.

1754
02:12:59,440 --> 02:13:00,740
Trained us.

1755
02:13:01,280 --> 02:13:03,630
But my father could not accept Bane.

1756
02:13:04,480 --> 02:13:05,950
He saw only a monster.

1757
02:13:06,320 --> 02:13:11,269
His very existence was a reminder
of the hell he'd left his wife to die in.

1758
02:13:12,360 --> 02:13:14,990
He excommunicated Bane
from the League of Shadows.

1759
02:13:15,520 --> 02:13:19,350
His only crime was that he loved me.

1760
02:13:21,600 --> 02:13:24,060
I could not forgive my father.

1761
02:13:28,840 --> 02:13:30,240
Until you murdered him.

1762
02:13:33,920 --> 02:13:35,250
[BEEPING]

1763
02:13:47,560 --> 02:13:52,160
He was trying to kill millions
of innocent people.

1764
02:13:53,080 --> 02:13:56,130
Innocent is a strong word
to throw around Gotham, Bruce.

1765
02:13:59,080 --> 02:14:01,640
I honor my father by finishing his work.

1766
02:14:13,680 --> 02:14:17,790
Vengeance against the man who killed him
is simply a reward for my patience.

1767
02:14:19,800 --> 02:14:20,710
You see...

1768
02:14:22,320 --> 02:14:23,440
it's the slow knife...

1769
02:14:23,760 --> 02:14:25,970
..the knife that takes its time.

1770
02:14:29,920 --> 02:14:30,930
The knife...

1771
02:14:31,880 --> 02:14:34,900
..that waits years without forgetting...

1772
02:14:35,600 --> 02:14:38,370
..then slips quietly between the bones.

1773
02:14:39,760 --> 02:14:40,840
That's the knife...

1774
02:14:42,280 --> 02:14:43,400
..that cuts deepest.

1775
02:14:43,720 --> 02:14:44,660
Please.

1776
02:14:45,160 --> 02:14:46,700
[DETONATOR CLICKS]

1777
02:14:52,200 --> 02:14:53,880
Maybe your knife...

1778
02:14:55,080 --> 02:14:56,269
..was too slow.

1779
02:14:56,600 --> 02:14:57,790
MERCENARY:
The truck is under attack.

1780
02:14:58,120 --> 02:15:01,280
Gordon.
You gave him a way to block my signal.

1781
02:15:01,880 --> 02:15:02,750
No matter.

1782
02:15:03,040 --> 02:15:04,550
[GRUNTS]

1783
02:15:05,320 --> 02:15:07,070
He's bought Gotham 11 minutes.

1784
02:15:07,560 --> 02:15:09,210
[BEEPING]

1785
02:15:11,520 --> 02:15:12,780
Come on!

1786
02:15:13,560 --> 02:15:14,750
This way!

1787
02:15:20,280 --> 02:15:22,309
COP:
Stay there! What are you doing?

1788
02:15:23,040 --> 02:15:25,850
Blake, MCU!
I'm getting these boys to safety!

1789
02:15:26,400 --> 02:15:27,519
You'll get us all killed!

1790
02:15:27,840 --> 02:15:30,370
If anyone crosses this bridge,
they'll blow the city!

1791
02:15:30,880 --> 02:15:33,720
It's gonna blow anyway!
We need to open this bridge, now!

1792
02:15:34,280 --> 02:15:36,950
Detective, if you take one step forward
we will shoot you!

1793
02:15:37,480 --> 02:15:40,500
If you take two steps forward,
we will blow the bridge!

1794
02:15:42,920 --> 02:15:45,690
Okay, go back by the bus and wait for me,
all right? Go back and wait.

1795
02:15:49,200 --> 02:15:52,530
TALIA: Prepare a convoy. We must secure
the bomb until it detonates.

1796
02:15:54,280 --> 02:15:57,400
Don't kill him,
I want him to feel the heat.

1797
02:15:58,560 --> 02:16:02,670
Feel the fire of 12 million souls you failed.

1798
02:16:08,920 --> 02:16:10,220
Goodbye, my friend.

1799
02:16:18,160 --> 02:16:19,320
BANE:
Goodbye.

1800
02:16:20,000 --> 02:16:22,950
Keep moving forward!
Flank them at the stairs!

1801
02:16:31,240 --> 02:16:32,709
Shoot them.

1802
02:16:33,559 --> 02:16:34,789
Shoot them all.

1803
02:16:35,120 --> 02:16:36,280
[GUNFIRE]

1804
02:16:43,799 --> 02:16:46,849
BANE:
We both know that I have to kill you now.

1805
02:16:50,080 --> 02:16:51,940
You'll just have to imagine the fire.

1806
02:16:56,240 --> 02:16:57,750
[PANTING]

1807
02:16:59,719 --> 02:17:01,439
About the whole no-guns thing...

1808
02:17:02,600 --> 02:17:05,160
..['m not sure I feel as strongly
about it as you do.

1809
02:17:18,360 --> 02:17:19,730
Pull up.

1810
02:17:22,520 --> 02:17:23,710
Stay level.

1811
02:17:35,760 --> 02:17:38,530
We have to force that convoy east
to the entrance to the reactor.

1812
02:17:40,680 --> 02:17:43,210
I need you on the ground,
I'll be in the air. Go.

1813
02:17:43,799 --> 02:17:46,539
The situation has changed.
Your orders are out of date.

1814
02:17:47,600 --> 02:17:50,510
I'm a cop, like you,
and I'm walking out there.

1815
02:17:51,719 --> 02:17:53,469
Please do not shoot me!

1816
02:17:55,600 --> 02:17:56,540
Shoot at his feet.

1817
02:18:06,280 --> 02:18:08,240
Nothing like a little air superiority.

1818
02:18:08,680 --> 02:18:10,430
Detective! Please stop!

1819
02:18:11,240 --> 02:18:13,840
Please, detective! Stop!

1820
02:18:14,360 --> 02:18:15,900
Stop walking!

1821
02:18:16,959 --> 02:18:19,240
Blow it! Do it!

1822
02:18:30,400 --> 02:18:32,400
You have to get that bomb here.
You've got 10 minutes.

1823
02:18:43,200 --> 02:18:45,130
They're pushing us
to the entrance of the reactor.

1824
02:18:45,559 --> 02:18:47,629
They're gonna try to reconnect the core.

1825
02:18:49,160 --> 02:18:50,459
You idiots!

1826
02:18:50,920 --> 02:18:52,430
You sons of bitches!

1827
02:18:52,799 --> 02:18:54,269
You're killing us!

1828
02:18:54,639 --> 02:18:56,010
Yeah, follow your orders!

1829
02:18:56,559 --> 02:18:58,490
All right, boys. Get in a circle.
Bow your heads.

1830
02:19:01,559 --> 02:19:03,070
It's on my side.

1831
02:19:38,360 --> 02:19:39,760
[PANEL BEEPING]

1832
02:19:46,240 --> 02:19:47,469
[BEEPING]

1833
02:19:49,280 --> 02:19:51,910
BLAKE: Hey, Father! Let's get everyone
back on the bus, okay? Go, go, go!

1834
02:19:52,440 --> 02:19:55,110
-Back on the bus!
-There's nowhere to go.

1835
02:19:56,000 --> 02:19:56,870
On the bus!

1836
02:20:51,560 --> 02:20:53,350
FOX:
You've got to turn the truck east!

1837
02:20:58,320 --> 02:20:59,789
Stay straight!

1838
02:21:11,120 --> 02:21:12,200
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

1839
02:21:30,440 --> 02:21:33,280
Give me a hand!
We can get a cable on it!

1840
02:21:40,160 --> 02:21:42,550
Fox showed me how to override
the reactor.

1841
02:21:46,480 --> 02:21:47,529
Oh, dear.

1842
02:21:48,040 --> 02:21:49,790
[ALARM WAILING]

1843
02:21:51,240 --> 02:21:54,050
Including the emergency flood.

1844
02:22:10,160 --> 02:22:11,770
TALIA:
There's no way...

1845
02:22:12,880 --> 02:22:13,929
this bomb...

1846
02:22:14,920 --> 02:22:16,220
.. Will be stopped.

1847
02:22:17,560 --> 02:22:18,500
What are you doing?

1848
02:22:18,800 --> 02:22:20,800
Protection from the blast.
We're gonna be all right!

1849
02:22:21,240 --> 02:22:22,320
It's an atom bomb!

1850
02:22:22,640 --> 02:22:24,890
Think they need to hear that?
Let them die without hope? Come on!

1851
02:22:26,080 --> 02:22:27,480
Prepare yourselves.

1852
02:22:29,320 --> 02:22:31,039
My father's work...

1853
02:22:32,480 --> 02:22:33,880
«jis done.

1854
02:22:39,640 --> 02:22:42,099
GORDON: What are you doing?
BATMAN: I can get it out over the bay!

1855
02:22:42,880 --> 02:22:44,740
CATWOMAN:
Set it to fly out over the water, then eject?

1856
02:22:45,160 --> 02:22:46,530
BATMAN:
No autopilot.

1857
02:22:48,280 --> 02:22:51,120
You could've gone anywhere,
been anything. But you came back here.

1858
02:22:51,680 --> 02:22:52,620
So did you.

1859
02:22:53,200 --> 02:22:54,920
I guess we're both suckers.

1860
02:23:02,520 --> 02:23:04,910
-l never cared who you were.
-And you were right.

1861
02:23:05,400 --> 02:23:07,570
Shouldn't the people know
the hero who saved them?

1862
02:23:08,040 --> 02:23:09,020
A hero can be anyone.

1863
02:23:09,320 --> 02:23:11,779
Even a man doing something
as simple and reassuring...

1864
02:23:12,280 --> 02:23:15,540
..as putting a coat around a young boy's
shoulders to let him know...

1865
02:23:16,160 --> 02:23:17,670
..the world hadn't ended.

1866
02:23:34,880 --> 02:23:36,109
Bruce Wayne?

1867
02:23:48,840 --> 02:23:51,470
Come on! There you go!
Okay, you too. Come on, Father.

1868
02:24:10,320 --> 02:24:11,900
Hey, heads down! This is it!

1869
02:24:12,440 --> 02:24:14,900
-No.
-No, that's Batman!

1870
02:24:53,440 --> 02:24:55,190
[BEEPING]

1871
02:25:01,480 --> 02:25:02,560
That's detonation!

1872
02:25:09,880 --> 02:25:11,490
It's out over the bay! Clear of the city!

1873
02:25:11,920 --> 02:25:13,950
[CHEERING]

1874
02:25:30,760 --> 02:25:33,150
GORDON:
“Il see a beautiful city...

1875
02:25:33,640 --> 02:25:35,430
and a brilliant people...

1876
02:25:35,920 --> 02:25:37,600
..tising from this abyss.

1877
02:25:39,000 --> 02:25:42,370
1 see the lives for which
I lay down my life...

1878
02:25:43,240 --> 02:25:44,250
-. peaceful...

1879
02:25:45,120 --> 02:25:47,860
.. useful, prosperous and happy.

1880
02:25:50,600 --> 02:25:53,650
1 see that I hold a sanctuary
in their hearts...

1881
02:25:55,840 --> 02:25:58,510
-and in the hearts
of their descendants...

1882
02:25:59,680 --> 02:26:01,120
..generations hence.

1883
02:26:03,920 --> 02:26:07,470
It is a far, far better thing that I do...

1884
02:26:08,800 --> 02:26:10,449
..than I have ever done.

1885
02:26:11,680 --> 02:26:15,470
It is a far, far better rest that I go to...

1886
02:26:18,800 --> 02:26:20,240
..than I have ever known."

1887
02:26:35,200 --> 02:26:37,020
[ALFRED SOBBING]

1888
02:26:38,040 --> 02:26:39,230
ALFRED:
I'm so sorry.

1889
02:26:39,760 --> 02:26:41,200
I failed you.

1890
02:26:43,360 --> 02:26:44,730
You trusted me...

1891
02:26:46,440 --> 02:26:47,380
«and I failed you.

1892
02:26:51,480 --> 02:26:52,990
Can I change your mind...

1893
02:26:55,440 --> 02:26:57,050
..about quitting the force?

1894
02:26:58,160 --> 02:27:01,390
You know what you said about
structures becoming shackles?

1895
02:27:02,200 --> 02:27:05,180
You were right, and I can't take it.
The injustice.

1896
02:27:05,800 --> 02:27:09,420
I mean, no one's ever gonna know
who saved an entire city.

1897
02:27:10,120 --> 02:27:11,030
They know.

1898
02:27:13,000 --> 02:27:14,440
It was the Batman.

1899
02:27:31,960 --> 02:27:34,980
LAWYER: Mr. Wayne's will was not amended
to reflect his more modest estate.

1900
02:27:35,560 --> 02:27:38,789
Nonetheless, there are considerable
assets to dispose of.

1901
02:27:39,400 --> 02:27:42,310
The contents of the house are to be sold
to settle the estate's accounts...

1902
02:27:42,880 --> 02:27:46,529
and the remainder is left in its entirety
to Alfred J. Pennyworth.

1903
02:27:48,440 --> 02:27:52,550
The house and grounds are left to
the city of Gotham on condition that...

1904
02:27:53,280 --> 02:27:56,400
..they never be demolished,
altered or otherwise interfered with...

1905
02:27:57,000 --> 02:28:00,190
..and that they shall be used for
one purpose, and one purpose only:

1906
02:28:02,240 --> 02:28:05,820
The housing and care of the city’s
at-risk and orphaned children.

1907
02:28:06,880 --> 02:28:10,640
My clerk can help with the smaller
correspondences and instructions.

1908
02:28:11,320 --> 02:28:12,510
BLAKE:
Blake, John.

1909
02:28:12,960 --> 02:28:15,699
-Nothing here.
-Uh, try my legal name.

1910
02:28:19,360 --> 02:28:21,710
You should use your full name.
I like that name.

1911
02:28:22,200 --> 02:28:23,780
-Robin.
-Thanks.

1912
02:28:24,160 --> 02:28:25,980
SCIENTIST 1: Why worry about
the stabilization software?

1913
02:28:26,400 --> 02:28:28,080
This entire autopilot system's
completely obsolete.

1914
02:28:28,480 --> 02:28:31,670
Please, I just need to know
what I could've done to fix it.

1915
02:28:32,280 --> 02:28:35,760
But, Mr. Fox, it's already been fixed.
Software patch. Six months ago.

1916
02:28:36,400 --> 02:28:37,730
Check the ID on the patch.

1917
02:28:40,880 --> 02:28:42,210
SCIENTIST 2:
Bruce Wayne.

1918
02:28:43,240 --> 02:28:45,170
-Any news on the missing item?
-Not yet.

1919
02:28:45,600 --> 02:28:46,790
They better leave no stone unturned.

1920
02:28:47,120 --> 02:28:50,000
We can't leave a string of pearls
on the manifest as lost.

1921
02:37:44,040 --> 02:37:45,720
[English - US - SDH]

